#. class="division">
msgctxt "dn23:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 23"
msgstr "Long Discourses 23"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn23:2.1"
msgid "Pāyāsisutta"
msgstr "With Pāyāsi"

#. </h1></div><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.316"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:3.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn23:3.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā kumārakassapo kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā "
"bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi yena setabyā nāma "
"kosalānaṃ nagaraṃ tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Kumāra Kassapa was wandering in the land of the "
"Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of five hundred mendicants when he "
"arrived at at a Kosalan citadel named Setavyā."

#. VAR: siṃsapāvane → sīsapāvane (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā kumārakassapo setabyāyaṃ viharati uttarena setabyaṃ "
"siṃsapāvane."
msgstr "He stayed on in the grove of Indian Rosewood to the north of Setavyā."

msgctxt "dn23:3.4"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena pāyāsi rājañño setabyaṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ "
"satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ raññā pasenadinā kosalena dinnaṃ "
"rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the chieftain Pāyāsi was living in Setavyā. It was a crown "
"property given by King Pasenadi of Kosala, teeming with living creatures, "
"full of hay, wood, water, and grain, a royal endowment of the highest "
"quality."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:4.1"
msgid "1. Pāyāsirājaññavatthu"
msgstr "On Pāyāsi"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.317"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena pāyāsissa rājaññassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ "
"uppannaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "Now at that time Pāyāsi had the following harmful misconception:"

msgctxt "dn23:5.2"
msgid ""
"“itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There’s no afterlife. No beings are reborn spontaneously. There’s no fruit "
"or result of good and bad deeds.”"

msgctxt "dn23:5.3"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho setabyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:"
msgstr "The brahmins and householders of Setavyā heard:"

msgctxt "dn23:5.4"
msgid ""
"“samaṇo khalu bho kumārakassapo samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako kosalesu cārikaṃ "
"caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi setabyaṃ "
"anuppatto setabyāyaṃ viharati uttarena setabyaṃ siṃsapāvane."
msgstr ""
"“It seems the ascetic Kumāra Kassapa—a disciple of the ascetic Gotama—is "
"staying in the grove of Indian Rosewood to the north of Setavyā."

msgctxt "dn23:5.5"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ kumārakassapaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:"
msgstr "He has this good reputation:"

#. VAR: vuddho → vudho (bj) | buddho (s1-3, km, mr) | vuḍḍho (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:5.6"
msgid ""
"‘paṇḍito byatto medhāvī bahussuto cittakathī kalyāṇapaṭibhāno vuddho ceva "
"arahā ca."
msgstr ""
"‘He is astute, competent, intelligent, learned, a brilliant speaker, "
"eloquent, mature, a perfected one.’"

msgctxt "dn23:5.7"
msgid "Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī’”ti."
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.”"

#. VAR: yena siṃsapāvanaṃ → yena sīsapāvanaṃ (s1-3, km) | tenu­pasaṃ­kamanti
#. (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:5.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho setabyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā setabyāya nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī "
"gaṇībhūtā uttarenamukhā gacchanti yena siṃsapāvanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then, having departed Setavyā, they formed into companies and headed north "
"to the grove."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena pāyāsi rājañño uparipāsāde divāseyyaṃ upagato hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the chieftain Pāyāsi had retired to the upper floor of his "
"stilt longhouse for his midday nap."

#. VAR: yena siṃsapāvanaṃ → tenu­pasaṃ­kamante (pts1)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn23:6.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho pāyāsi rājañño setabyake brāhmaṇagahapatike setabyāya nikkhamitvā "
"saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūte uttarenamukhe gacchante yena siṃsapāvanaṃ, disvā "
"khattaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"He saw the brahmins and householders heading north towards the grove, and "
"addressed his steward:"

msgctxt "dn23:6.3"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ nu kho, bho khatte, setabyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā setabyāya nikkhamitvā "
"saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūtā uttarenamukhā gacchanti yena siṃsapāvanan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“My steward, why are the brahmins and householders headed north towards the "
"grove?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.318"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Atthi kho, bho, samaṇo kumārakassapo, samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako kosalesu "
"cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi "
"setabyaṃ anuppatto setabyāyaṃ viharati uttarena setabyaṃ siṃsapāvane."
msgstr ""
"“The ascetic Kumāra Kassapa—a disciple of the ascetic Gotama—is staying in "
"the grove of Indian Rosewood to the north of Setavyā."

msgctxt "dn23:7.2"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ kumārakassapaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:"
msgstr "He has this good reputation:"

#. VAR: arahā cā’ti → arahā ca (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘paṇḍito byatto medhāvī bahussuto cittakathī kalyāṇapaṭibhāno vuddho ceva "
"arahā cā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘He is astute, competent, intelligent, learned, a brilliant speaker, "
"eloquent, mature, a perfected one.’"

#. VAR: Tamete → tamenaṃ te (bj, mr) | tamenaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:7.4"
msgid "Tamete bhavantaṃ kumārakassapaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamantī”ti."
msgstr "They’re going to see that Kumāra Kassapa.”"

msgctxt "dn23:7.5"
msgid "“Tena hi, bho khatte, yena setabyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā tenupasaṅkama;"
msgstr "“Well then, go to the brahmins and householders and"

msgctxt "dn23:7.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā setabyake brāhmaṇagahapatike evaṃ vadehi:"
msgstr "say to them:"

msgctxt "dn23:7.7"
msgid "‘pāyāsi, bho, rājañño evamāha—"
msgstr "‘Sirs, the chieftain Pāyāsi asks"

msgctxt "dn23:7.8"
msgid ""
"āgamentu kira bhavanto, pāyāsipi rājañño samaṇaṃ kumārakassapaṃ dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamissatī’ti."
msgstr "you to wait, as he will also go to see the ascetic Kumāra Kassapa.’"

msgctxt "dn23:7.9"
msgid ""
"Purā samaṇo kumārakassapo setabyake brāhmaṇagahapatike bāle abyatte "
"saññāpeti:"
msgstr ""
"Before Kumāra Kassapa convinces those foolish and incompetent brahmins and "
"householders that"

msgctxt "dn23:7.10"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’ti."
msgstr ""
"there is an afterlife, there are beings reborn spontaneously, and there is a "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds—"

msgctxt "dn23:7.11"
msgid ""
"Natthi hi, bho khatte, paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi "
"sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”ti."
msgstr "for none of these things are true!”"

msgctxt "dn23:7.12"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho so khattā pāyāsissa rājaññassa paṭissutvā yena setabyakā "
"brāhmaṇagahapatikā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied the steward, and did as he was asked."

msgctxt "dn23:7.13"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā setabyake brāhmaṇagahapatike etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:7.14"
msgid ""
"“pāyāsi, bho, rājañño evamāha, āgamentu kira bhavanto, pāyāsipi rājañño "
"samaṇaṃ kumārakassapaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.319"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:8.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pāyāsi rājañño setabyakehi brāhmaṇagahapatikehi parivuto yena "
"siṃsapāvanaṃ yenāyasmā kumārakassapo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then Pāyāsi escorted by the brahmins and householders, went up to Kumāra "
"Kassapa,"

msgctxt "dn23:8.2"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā kumārakassapena saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ "
"sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"and exchanged greetings with him. When the greetings and polite conversation "
"were over, he sat down to one side."

msgctxt "dn23:8.3"
msgid ""
"Setabyakāpi kho brāhmaṇagahapatikā appekacce āyasmantaṃ kumārakassapaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Before sitting down to one side, some of the brahmins and householders of "
"Setavyā bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held "
"up their cupped palms toward Kumāra Kassapa, some announced their name and "
"clan, while some kept silent."

msgctxt "dn23:8.4"
msgid "appekacce āyasmatā kumārakassapena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:8.5"
msgid "sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:8.6"
msgid ""
"Appekacce yenāyasmā kumārakassapo tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:8.7"
msgid "Appekacce nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:8.8"
msgid "Appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:9.1"
msgid "2. Natthikavāda"
msgstr "Nihilism"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:10.1"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho pāyāsi rājañño āyasmantaṃ kumārakassapaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Seated to one side, the chieftain Pāyāsi said to Venerable Kumāra Kassapa:"

msgctxt "dn23:10.2"
msgid "“ahañhi, bho kassapa, evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhī:"
msgstr "“Master Kassapa, this is my doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn23:10.3"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘There’s no afterlife. No beings are reborn spontaneously. There’s no fruit "
"or result of good and bad deeds.’”"

msgctxt "dn23:10.4"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, rājañña, evaṃvādiṃ evaṃdiṭṭhiṃ addasaṃ vā assosiṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“Well, chieftain, I’ve never seen or heard of anyone holding such a doctrine "
"or view."

msgctxt "dn23:10.5"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "For how on earth can anyone say such a thing?"

msgctxt "dn23:10.6"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:11.1"
msgid "2.1. Candimasūriyaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Moon and Sun"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:12.1"
msgid ""
"Tena hi, rājañña, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi, yathā te khameyya, tathā naṃ "
"byākareyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"Well then, chieftain, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer "
"as you like."

msgctxt "dn23:12.2"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājañña, ime candimasūriyā imasmiṃ vā loke parasmiṃ vā, "
"devā vā te manussā vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What do you think, chieftain? Are the moon and sun in this world or the "
"other world? Are they gods or humans?”"

msgctxt "dn23:12.3"
msgid "“Ime, bho kassapa, candimasūriyā parasmiṃ loke, na imasmiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“They are in the other world, Master Kassapa, and they are gods, not humans.”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn23:12.4"
msgid "devā te na manussā”ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:12.5"
msgid "“Imināpi kho te, rājañña, pariyāyena evaṃ hotu—"
msgstr "“By this method it ought to be proven that"

msgctxt "dn23:12.6"
msgid ""
"itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”ti."
msgstr ""
"there is an afterlife, there are beings reborn spontaneously, and there is a "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.320"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:13.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho evaṃ me ettha hoti:"
msgstr "“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I think that"

msgctxt "dn23:13.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr ""
"there’s no afterlife, no beings are reborn spontaneously, and there’s no "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds.”"

msgctxt "dn23:13.3"
msgid "“Atthi pana, rājañña, pariyāyo, yena te pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“Is there a method by which you can prove what you say?”"

msgctxt "dn23:13.4"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:13.5"
msgid "“Atthi, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“There is, Master Kassapa.”"

msgctxt "dn23:13.6"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:13.7"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ viya, rājaññā”ti?"
msgstr "“How, exactly, chieftain?”"

msgctxt "dn23:13.8"
msgid ""
"“Idha me, bho kassapa, mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī "
"kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavācā pharusavācā samphappalāpī abhijjhālū "
"byāpannacittā micchādiṭṭhī."
msgstr ""
"“Well, I have friends and colleagues, relatives and kin who kill living "
"creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s "
"lying, divisive, harsh, and meaningless. And they’re covetous, malicious, "
"with wrong view."

msgctxt "dn23:13.9"
msgid "Te aparena samayena ābādhikā honti dukkhitā bāḷhagilānā."
msgstr "Sooner or later they become sick, suffering, gravely ill."

msgctxt "dn23:13.10"
msgid "Yadāhaṃ jānāmi:"
msgstr "When I know that"

msgctxt "dn23:13.11"
msgid ""
"‘na dānime imamhā ābādhā vuṭṭhahissantī’ti tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "they will not recover from their illness, I go to them and say:"

msgctxt "dn23:13.12"
msgid "‘santi kho, bho, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr ""
"‘Sirs, there are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn23:13.13"
msgid ""
"“ye te pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavācā "
"pharusavācā samphappalāpī abhijjhālū byāpannacittā micchādiṭṭhī, te kāyassa "
"bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Those who kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct; uses "
"speech that’s lying, divisive, harsh, and meaningless; and are covetous, "
"malicious, and has wrong view—when their body breaks up, after death, are "
"reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.”"

msgctxt "dn23:13.14"
msgid ""
"Bhavanto kho pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavācā "
"pharusavācā samphappalāpī abhijjhālū byāpannacittā micchādiṭṭhī."
msgstr "You do all these things."

msgctxt "dn23:13.15"
msgid ""
"Sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ, bhavanto kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissanti."
msgstr ""
"If what those ascetics and brahmins say is true, when your body breaks up, "
"after death, you’ll be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the "
"underworld, hell."

msgctxt "dn23:13.16"
msgid ""
"Sace, bho, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjeyyātha, yena me āgantvā āroceyyātha:"
msgstr "If that happens, sirs, come and tell me that"

msgctxt "dn23:13.17"
msgid ""
"“itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”ti."
msgstr ""
"there is an afterlife, there are beings reborn spontaneously, and there is a "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds."

msgctxt "dn23:13.18"
msgid ""
"Bhavanto kho pana me saddhāyikā paccayikā, yaṃ bhavantehi diṭṭhaṃ, yathā "
"sāmaṃ diṭṭhaṃ evametaṃ bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I trust you and believe you. Anything you see will be just as if I’ve seen "
"it for myself.’"

msgctxt "dn23:13.19"
msgid ""
"Te me ‘sādhū’ti paṭissutvā neva āgantvā ārocenti, na pana dūtaṃ pahiṇanti."
msgstr ""
"They agree to this. But they don’t come back to tell me, nor do they send a "
"messenger."

msgctxt "dn23:13.20"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "This is the method by which I prove that"

msgctxt "dn23:13.21"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr ""
"there’s no afterlife, no beings are reborn spontaneously, and there’s no "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:14.1"
msgid "2.2. Coraupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Bandit"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wp" id="wp7"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.322"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:15.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi."
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I’ll ask you about this in return,"

msgctxt "dn23:15.2"
msgid "Yathā te khameyya tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi."
msgstr "and you can answer as you like."

msgctxt "dn23:15.3"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājañña, idha te purisā coraṃ āgucāriṃ gahetvā dasseyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"What do you think, chieftain? Suppose they were to arrest a bandit, a "
"criminal and present him to you, saying:"

msgctxt "dn23:15.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ te, bhante, coro āgucārī;"
msgstr "‘Sir, this is a bandit, a criminal."

msgctxt "dn23:15.5"
msgid "imassa yaṃ icchasi, taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti."
msgstr "Punish him as you will.’"

msgctxt "dn23:15.6"
msgid "Te tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Then you’d say to them:"

#. VAR: rathikāya rathikaṃ → rathiyāya rathiyaṃ (bahūsu)
#. VAR: karitvā → kāretvā (bj, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:15.7"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, imaṃ purisaṃ daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ "
"bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathikāya rathikaṃ "
"siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhamitvā dakkhiṇato "
"nagarassa āghātane sīsaṃ chindathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, my men, tie this man’s arms tightly behind his back with a "
"strong rope. Shave his head and march him from street to street and square "
"to square to the beating of a harsh drum. Then take him out the south gate "
"and there, at the place of execution to the south of the city, chop off his "
"head.’"

# RD gets this right, MW does not.
msgctxt "dn23:15.8"
msgid ""
"Te ‘sādhū’ti paṭissutvā taṃ purisaṃ daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ "
"gāḷhabandhanaṃ bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathikāya "
"rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhamitvā "
"dakkhiṇato nagarassa āghātane nisīdāpeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Saying, ‘Good,’ they’d do as they were told, sitting him down at the place "
"of execution."

msgctxt "dn23:15.9"
msgid "Labheyya nu kho so coro coraghātesu:"
msgstr "Could that bandit get the executioners to wait, saying:"

# Follow PTS reading uddassetva, which at MN 82 has the sense "visit".
msgctxt "dn23:15.10"
msgid ""
"‘āgamentu tāva bhavanto coraghātā, amukasmiṃ me gāme vā nigame vā mittāmaccā "
"ñātisālohitā, yāvāhaṃ tesaṃ uddisitvā āgacchāmī’ti, udāhu vippalapantasseva "
"coraghātā sīsaṃ chindeyyun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Please, good executioners! I have friends and colleagues, relatives and kin "
"in such and such village or town. Wait until I’ve visited them, then I’ll "
"come back’? Or would they just chop off his head as he prattled on?”"

msgctxt "dn23:15.11"
msgid "“Na hi so, bho kassapa, coro labheyya coraghātesu:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:15.12"
msgid ""
"‘āgamentu tāva bhavanto coraghātā amukasmiṃ me gāme vā nigame vā mittāmaccā "
"ñātisālohitā, yāvāhaṃ tesaṃ uddisitvā āgacchāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:15.13"
msgid "Atha kho naṃ vippalapantasseva coraghātā sīsaṃ chindeyyun”ti."
msgstr "“They’d just chop off his head.”"

msgctxt "dn23:15.14"
msgid ""
"“So hi nāma, rājañña, coro manusso manussabhūtesu coraghātesu na labhissati:"
msgstr ""
"“So even a human bandit couldn’t get his human executioners to stay his "
"execution."

msgctxt "dn23:15.15"
msgid ""
"‘āgamentu tāva bhavanto coraghātā, amukasmiṃ me gāme vā nigame vā mittāmaccā "
"ñātisālohitā, yāvāhaṃ tesaṃ uddisitvā āgacchāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:15.16"
msgid ""
"Kiṃ pana te mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī "
"musāvādī pisuṇavācā pharusavācā samphappalāpī abhijjhālū byāpannacittā "
"micchādiṭṭhī, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapannā labhissanti nirayapālesu:"
msgstr ""
"What then of your friends and colleagues, relatives and kin who are reborn "
"in a lower realm after doing bad things? Could they get the wardens of hell "
"to wait, saying:"

msgctxt "dn23:15.17"
msgid ""
"‘āgamentu tāva bhavanto nirayapālā, yāva mayaṃ pāyāsissa rājaññassa gantvā "
"ārocema:"
msgstr ""
"‘Please, good wardens of hell! Wait until I’ve gone to the chieftain Pāyāsi "
"to tell him that"

msgctxt "dn23:15.18"
msgid ""
"“itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”’ti?"
msgstr ""
"there is an afterlife, there are beings reborn spontaneously, and there is a "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds’?”"

msgctxt "dn23:15.19"
msgid "Imināpi kho te, rājañña, pariyāyena evaṃ hotu:"
msgstr "By this method, too, it ought to be proven that"

msgctxt "dn23:15.20"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr ""
"there is an afterlife, there are beings reborn spontaneously, and there is a "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wp" id="wp8"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.323"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:16.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho evaṃ me ettha hoti:"
msgstr "“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I think that"

msgctxt "dn23:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

msgctxt "dn23:16.3"
msgid "“Atthi pana, rājañña, pariyāyo yena te pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“Is there a method by which you can prove what you say?”"

msgctxt "dn23:16.4"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:16.5"
msgid "“Atthi, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“There is, Master Kassapa.”"

msgctxt "dn23:16.6"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:16.7"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ viya, rājaññā”ti?"
msgstr "“How, exactly, chieftain?”"

msgctxt "dn23:16.8"
msgid ""
"“Idha me, bho kassapa, mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā "
"adinnādānā paṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā "
"pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratā pharusāya vācāya paṭiviratā samphappalāpā "
"paṭiviratā anabhijjhālū abyāpannacittā sammādiṭṭhī."
msgstr ""
"“Well, I have friends and colleagues, relatives and kin who refrain from "
"killing living creatures, stealing, and committing sexual misconduct. They "
"refrain from speech that’s lying, divisive, harsh, and meaningless. And they’"
"re content, kind-hearted, with right view."

msgctxt "dn23:16.9"
msgid "Te aparena samayena ābādhikā honti dukkhitā bāḷhagilānā."
msgstr "Sooner or later they become sick, suffering, gravely ill."

msgctxt "dn23:16.10"
msgid "Yadāhaṃ jānāmi:"
msgstr "When I know that"

msgctxt "dn23:16.11"
msgid ""
"‘na dānime imamhā ābādhā vuṭṭhahissantī’ti tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "they will not recover from their illness, I go to them and say:"

msgctxt "dn23:16.12"
msgid "‘santi kho, bho, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr ""
"‘Sirs, there are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn23:16.13"
msgid ""
"“ye te pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā adinnādānā paṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā "
"paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratā pharusāya vācāya "
"paṭiviratā samphappalāpā paṭiviratā anabhijjhālū abyāpannacittā sammādiṭṭhī "
"te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Those who refrain from killing living creaturesand have, stealing, and "
"committing sexual misconduct; who refrain from speech that’s lying, "
"divisive, harsh, and meaningless, and are content, kind-hearted, with right "
"view—when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a "
"heavenly realm.”"

msgctxt "dn23:16.14"
msgid ""
"Bhavanto kho pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā adinnādānā paṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā "
"paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratā pharusāya vācāya "
"paṭiviratā samphappalāpā paṭiviratā anabhijjhālū abyāpannacittā sammādiṭṭhī."
msgstr "You do all these things."

msgctxt "dn23:16.15"
msgid ""
"Sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ, bhavanto kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissanti."
msgstr ""
"If what those ascetics and brahmins say is true, when your body breaks up, "
"after death, you’ll be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "dn23:16.16"
msgid ""
"Sace, bho, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyātha, "
"yena me āgantvā āroceyyātha:"
msgstr "If that happens, sirs, come and tell me that"

msgctxt "dn23:16.17"
msgid ""
"“itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”ti."
msgstr "there is an afterlife."

msgctxt "dn23:16.18"
msgid ""
"Bhavanto kho pana me saddhāyikā paccayikā, yaṃ bhavantehi diṭṭhaṃ, yathā "
"sāmaṃ diṭṭhaṃ evametaṃ bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I trust you and believe you. Anything you see will be just as if I’ve seen "
"it for myself.’"

msgctxt "dn23:16.19"
msgid ""
"Te me ‘sādhū’ti paṭissutvā neva āgantvā ārocenti, na pana dūtaṃ pahiṇanti."
msgstr ""
"They agree to this. But they don’t come back to tell me, nor do they send a "
"messenger."

msgctxt "dn23:16.20"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "This is the method by which I prove that"

msgctxt "dn23:16.21"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:17.1"
msgid "2.3. Gūthakūpapurisaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Sewer"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wp" id="wp9"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.325"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:18.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi."
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile."

#. VAR: Upamāya midhekacce → upamāyapi idhekacce (bj, pts1) |
#. upamāya­pi­dhekacce (s1) | upamāya­pī­dhekacce (s1, s2, km)
msgctxt "dn23:18.2"
msgid "Upamāya midhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said. "

#. VAR: sasīsakaṃ → sasīsako (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:18.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājañña, puriso gūthakūpe sasīsakaṃ nimuggo assa."
msgstr "Suppose there was a man sunk over his head in a sewer."

msgctxt "dn23:18.4"
msgid "Atha tvaṃ purise āṇāpeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Then you were to order someone"

msgctxt "dn23:18.5"
msgid "‘tena hi, bho, taṃ purisaṃ tamhā gūthakūpā uddharathā’ti."
msgstr "to pull him out of the sewer,"

msgctxt "dn23:18.6"
msgid "Te ‘sādhū’ti paṭissutvā taṃ purisaṃ tamhā gūthakūpā uddhareyyuṃ."
msgstr "and they’d agree to do so."

msgctxt "dn23:18.7"
msgid "Te tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Then you’d tell them to"

msgctxt "dn23:18.8"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, tassa purisassa kāyā veḷupesikāhi gūthaṃ sunimmajjitaṃ "
"nimmajjathā’ti."
msgstr "carefully scrape the dung off that man’s body with bamboo scrapers,"

msgctxt "dn23:18.9"
msgid ""
"Te ‘sādhū’ti paṭissutvā tassa purisassa kāyā veḷupesikāhi gūthaṃ "
"sunimmajjitaṃ nimmajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr "and they’d agree to do so."

msgctxt "dn23:18.10"
msgid "Te tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Then you’d tell them to"

#. VAR: subbaṭṭitaṃ ubbaṭṭethā’ti → ubbaṭitaṃ ubbaṭethāti (s1-3, km) |
#. suppaṭṭitaṃ uppaṭṭethāti (mr)
msgctxt "dn23:18.11"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, tassa purisassa kāyaṃ paṇḍumattikāya tikkhattuṃ subbaṭṭitaṃ "
"ubbaṭṭethā’ti."
msgstr "carefully scrub that man’s body down with pale clay three times,"

msgctxt "dn23:18.12"
msgid ""
"Te tassa purisassa kāyaṃ paṇḍumattikāya tikkhattuṃ subbaṭṭitaṃ ubbaṭṭeyyuṃ."
msgstr "and they’d do so."

msgctxt "dn23:18.13"
msgid "Te tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Then you’d tell them to"

msgctxt "dn23:18.14"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, taṃ purisaṃ telena abbhañjitvā sukhumena cuṇṇena tikkhattuṃ "
"suppadhotaṃ karothā’ti."
msgstr ""
"smear that man’s body with oil, and carefully wash him down with fine paste "
"three times,"

msgctxt "dn23:18.15"
msgid ""
"Te taṃ purisaṃ telena abbhañjitvā sukhumena cuṇṇena tikkhattuṃ suppadhotaṃ "
"kareyyuṃ."
msgstr "and they’d do so."

msgctxt "dn23:18.16"
msgid "Te tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Then you’d tell them to"

msgctxt "dn23:18.17"
msgid "‘tena hi, bho, tassa purisassa kesamassuṃ kappethā’ti."
msgstr "dress that man’s hair and beard,"

msgctxt "dn23:18.18"
msgid "Te tassa purisassa kesamassuṃ kappeyyuṃ."
msgstr "and they’d do so."

msgctxt "dn23:18.19"
msgid "Te tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Then you’d tell them to"

msgctxt "dn23:18.20"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, tassa purisassa mahagghañca mālaṃ mahagghañca vilepanaṃ "
"mahagghāni ca vatthāni upaharathā’ti."
msgstr "provide that man with costly garlands, makeup, and clothes,"

msgctxt "dn23:18.21"
msgid ""
"Te tassa purisassa mahagghañca mālaṃ mahagghañca vilepanaṃ mahagghāni ca "
"vatthāni upahareyyuṃ."
msgstr "and they’d do so."

msgctxt "dn23:18.22"
msgid "Te tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Then you’d tell them to"

msgctxt "dn23:18.23"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, taṃ purisaṃ pāsādaṃ āropetvā pañcakāmaguṇāni upaṭṭhāpethā’ti."
msgstr ""
"bring that man up to the stilt longhouse and set him up with the five kinds "
"of sensual stimulation,"

msgctxt "dn23:18.24"
msgid "Te taṃ purisaṃ pāsādaṃ āropetvā pañcakāmaguṇāni upaṭṭhāpeyyuṃ."
msgstr "and they’d do so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.326"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:19.1"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājañña, api nu tassa purisassa sunhātassa suvilittassa "
"sukappitakesamassussa āmukkamālābharaṇassa odātavatthavasanassa "
"uparipāsādavaragatassa pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitassa samaṅgībhūtassa "
"paricārayamānassa punadeva tasmiṃ gūthakūpe nimujjitukāmatā assā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What do you think, chieftain? Now that man is nicely bathed and anointed, "
"with hair and beard dressed, bedecked with garlands and bracelets, dressed "
"in white, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation "
"upstairs in the stilt longhouse. Would he want to dive back into that sewer "
"again?”"

msgctxt "dn23:19.2"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho kassapa”."
msgstr "“No, Master Kassapa."

msgctxt "dn23:19.3"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn23:19.4"
msgid ""
"“Asuci, bho kassapa, gūthakūpo asuci ceva asucisaṅkhāto ca duggandho ca "
"duggandhasaṅkhāto ca jeguccho ca jegucchasaṅkhāto ca paṭikūlo ca "
"paṭikūlasaṅkhāto cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Because that sewer is filthy, stinking, disgusting, and repulsive, and it’s "
"regarded as such.”"

msgctxt "dn23:19.5"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, rājañña, manussā devānaṃ asucī ceva asucisaṅkhātā ca, "
"duggandhā ca duggandhasaṅkhātā ca, jegucchā ca jegucchasaṅkhātā ca, paṭikūlā "
"ca paṭikūlasaṅkhātā ca."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, chieftain, to the gods, human beings are filthy, stinking, "
"disgusting, and repulsive, and are regarded as such."

# Follow PTS reading ubbāhati. Cf. AN 3.93 for the sense "transport". RD had "ofends", while MW just omits this sentence.
msgctxt "dn23:19.6"
msgid "Yojanasataṃ kho, rājañña, manussagandho deve ubbādhati."
msgstr "The smell of humans reaches the gods even a hundred leagues away."

msgctxt "dn23:19.7"
msgid ""
"Kiṃ pana te mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā adinnādānā "
"paṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā pisuṇāya vācāya "
"paṭiviratā pharusāya vācāya paṭiviratā samphappalāpā paṭiviratā anabhijjhālū "
"abyāpannacittā sammādiṭṭhī, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapannā te āgantvā ārocessanti:"
msgstr ""
"What then of your friends and colleagues, relatives and kin who are reborn "
"in a higher realm after doing good things? Will they come back to tell you "
"that"

msgctxt "dn23:19.8"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’ti?"
msgstr "there is an afterlife?”"

msgctxt "dn23:19.9"
msgid "Imināpi kho te, rājañña, pariyāyena evaṃ hotu:"
msgstr "By this method, too, it ought to be proven that"

msgctxt "dn23:19.10"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there is an afterlife.”"

