"surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā, te aparena samayena ābādhikā honti "
"dukkhitā bāḷhagilānā."
msgstr ""
"“Well, I have friends and colleagues, relatives and kin who refrain from "
"killing living creatures and so on. Sooner or later they become sick, "
"suffering, gravely ill."

msgctxt "dn23:20.9"
msgid "Yadāhaṃ jānāmi:"
msgstr "When I know that"

msgctxt "dn23:20.10"
msgid ""
"‘na dānime imamhā ābādhā vuṭṭhahissantī’ti tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "they will not recover from their illness, I go to them and say:"

msgctxt "dn23:20.11"
msgid "‘santi kho, bho, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr ""
"‘Sirs, there are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn23:20.12"
msgid ""
"“ye te pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā adinnādānā paṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā "
"paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā, te "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti devānaṃ "
"tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Those who refrain from killing living creatures and so on are reborn in a "
"good place, a heavenly realm, in the company of the gods of the Thirty-"
"Three.”"

msgctxt "dn23:20.13"
msgid ""
"Bhavanto kho pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā adinnādānā paṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā "
"paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā."
msgstr "You do all these things."

msgctxt "dn23:20.14"
msgid ""
"Sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ, bhavanto kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissanti, devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ "
"sahabyataṃ."
msgstr ""
"If what those ascetics and brahmins say is true, when your body breaks up, "
"after death, you’ll be reborn in the company of the gods of the Thirty-Three."

msgctxt "dn23:20.15"
msgid ""
"Sace, bho, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyātha "
"devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ, yena me āgantvā āroceyyātha:"
msgstr "If that happens, sirs, come and tell me that"

msgctxt "dn23:20.16"
msgid ""
"“itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”ti."
msgstr "there is an afterlife."

msgctxt "dn23:20.17"
msgid ""
"Bhavanto kho pana me saddhāyikā paccayikā, yaṃ bhavantehi diṭṭhaṃ, yathā "
"sāmaṃ diṭṭhaṃ evametaṃ bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I trust you and believe you. Anything you see will be just as if I’ve seen "
"it for myself.’"

msgctxt "dn23:20.18"
msgid ""
"Te me ‘sādhū’ti paṭissutvā neva āgantvā ārocenti, na pana dūtaṃ pahiṇanti."
msgstr ""
"They agree to this. But they don’t come back to tell me, nor do they send a "
"messenger."

msgctxt "dn23:20.19"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "This is how I prove that"

msgctxt "dn23:20.20"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:21.1"
msgid "2.4. Tāvatiṃsadevaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Gods of the Thirty-Three"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wp" id="wp11"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.328"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:22.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi;"
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I’ll ask you about this in return,"

msgctxt "dn23:22.2"
msgid "yathā te khameyya, tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi."
msgstr "and you can answer as you like."

# 36,000,000 years, if anyone's counting.
#. VAR: rattindivo → rattidivo (mr)
#. VAR: mānussakaṃ → mānusakaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:22.3"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho pana, rājañña, mānussakaṃ vassasataṃ, devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ eso eko "
"rattindivo, tāya rattiyā tiṃsarattiyo māso, tena māsena dvādasamāsiyo "
"saṃvaccharo, tena saṃvaccharena dibbaṃ vassasahassaṃ devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ "
"āyuppamāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A hundred human years are equivalent to one day and night for the gods of "
"the Thirty-Three. Thirty such days make a month, and twelve months make a "
"year. The gods of the Thirty Three have a lifespan of a thousand such years."

msgctxt "dn23:22.4"
msgid ""
"Ye te mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā adinnādānā paṭiviratā "
"kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā "
"paṭiviratā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā "
"devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now, as to your friends who are reborn in the company of the gods of the "
"Thirty-Three after doing good things."

msgctxt "dn23:22.5"
msgid "Sace pana tesaṃ evaṃ bhavissati:"
msgstr "If they think:"

msgctxt "dn23:22.6"
msgid ""
"‘yāva mayaṃ dve vā tīṇi vā rattindivā dibbehi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā "
"samaṅgībhūtā paricārema, atha mayaṃ pāyāsissa rājaññassa gantvā āroceyyāma:"
msgstr ""
"‘First I’ll amuse myself for two or three days, supplied and provided with "
"the five kinds of heavenly sensual stimulation. Then I’ll go back to Pāyāsi "
"and tell him that"

msgctxt "dn23:22.7"
msgid ""
"“itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”ti."
msgstr "there is an afterlife.”"

msgctxt "dn23:22.8"
msgid "Api nu te āgantvā āroceyyuṃ—"
msgstr "Would they come back to tell you that"

msgctxt "dn23:22.9"
msgid ""
"itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti?"
msgstr "there is an afterlife?”"

msgctxt "dn23:22.10"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho kassapa."
msgstr "“No, Master Kassapa."

msgctxt "dn23:22.11"
msgid "Api hi mayaṃ, bho kassapa, ciraṃ kālaṅkatāpi bhaveyyāma."
msgstr "For I would be long dead by then."

msgctxt "dn23:22.12"
msgid "Ko panetaṃ bhoto kassapassa āroceti:"
msgstr "But Master Kassapa, who has told you"

msgctxt "dn23:22.13"
msgid "‘atthi devā tāvatiṃsā’ti vā ‘evaṃdīghāyukā devā tāvatiṃsā’ti vā."
msgstr ""
"that the gods of the Thirty-Three exist, or that they have such a long life "
"span?"

msgctxt "dn23:22.14"
msgid "Na mayaṃ bhoto kassapassa saddahāma:"
msgstr "I don’t believe you.”"

msgctxt "dn23:22.15"
msgid "‘atthi devā tāvatiṃsā’ti vā ‘evaṃdīghāyukā devā tāvatiṃsā’ti vā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:23.1"
msgid "2.5. Jaccandhaupamā"
msgstr "Blind From Birth"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.329"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn23:24.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, rājañña, jaccandho puriso na passeyya kaṇha—"
msgstr " "

#. VAR: mañjiṭṭhakāni → mañjeṭṭhikāni (bj) | mañjeṭṭhakāni (s1-3, km) |
#. mañjiṭṭhikāni (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:24.2"
msgid ""
"sukkāni rūpāni, na passeyya nīlakāni rūpāni, na passeyya pītakāni rūpāni, na "
"passeyya lohitakāni rūpāni, na passeyya mañjiṭṭhakāni rūpāni, na passeyya "
"samavisamaṃ, na passeyya tārakāni rūpāni, na passeyya candimasūriye."
msgstr ""
"“Chieftain, suppose there was a person blind from birth. They couldn’t see "
"sights that are dark or bright, or blue, yellow, red, or magenta. They "
"couldn’t see even and uneven ground, or the stars, or the moon and sun."

msgctxt "dn23:24.3"
msgid "So evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "They’d say: "

msgctxt "dn23:24.4"
msgid "‘natthi kaṇhasukkāni rūpāni, natthi kaṇhasukkānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr ""
"‘There’s no such thing as dark and bright sights, and no-one who sees them."

msgctxt "dn23:24.5"
msgid "Natthi nīlakāni rūpāni, natthi nīlakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr "There’s no such thing as blue,"

msgctxt "dn23:24.6"
msgid "Natthi pītakāni rūpāni, natthi pītakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr "yellow,"

msgctxt "dn23:24.7"
msgid "Natthi lohitakāni rūpāni, natthi lohitakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr "red,"

msgctxt "dn23:24.8"
msgid "Natthi mañjiṭṭhakāni rūpāni, natthi mañjiṭṭhakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr "magenta,"

msgctxt "dn23:24.9"
msgid "Natthi samavisamaṃ, natthi samavisamassa dassāvī."
msgstr "even and uneven ground,"

msgctxt "dn23:24.10"
msgid "Natthi tārakāni rūpāni, natthi tārakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr "stars,"

msgctxt "dn23:24.11"
msgid "Natthi candimasūriyā, natthi candimasūriyānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr "moon and sun, and no-one who sees these things."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn23:24.12"
msgid "Ahametaṃ na jānāmi, ahametaṃ na passāmi, tasmā taṃ natthī’ti."
msgstr "I don’t know it or see it, therefore it doesn’t exist.’"

msgctxt "dn23:24.13"
msgid "Sammā nu kho so, rājañña, vadamāno vadeyyā”ti?"
msgstr "Would they be speaking rightly?”"

msgctxt "dn23:24.14"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho kassapa."
msgstr "“No, Master Kassapa."

msgctxt "dn23:24.15"
msgid "Atthi kaṇhasukkāni rūpāni, atthi kaṇhasukkānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr "There are such things as dark and bright sights, and one who sees them."

msgctxt "dn23:24.16"
msgid "Atthi nīlakāni rūpāni, atthi nīlakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī …"
msgstr "And those other things are real, too,"

msgctxt "dn23:24.17"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:24.18"
msgid "atthi samavisamaṃ, atthi samavisamassa dassāvī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:24.19"
msgid "Atthi tārakāni rūpāni, atthi tārakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:24.20"
msgid "Atthi candimasūriyā, atthi candimasūriyānaṃ dassāvī."
msgstr "and one who sees them."

msgctxt "dn23:24.21"
msgid "‘Ahametaṃ na jānāmi, ahametaṃ na passāmi, tasmā taṃ natthī’ti."
msgstr ""
"So it’s not right to say this: ‘I don’t know it or see it, therefore it "
"doesn’t exist.’”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn23:24.22"
msgid "Na hi so, bho kassapa, sammā vadamāno vadeyyā”ti."
msgstr " "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:25.1"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho tvaṃ, rājañña, jaccandhūpamo maññe paṭibhāsi yaṃ maṃ tvaṃ evaṃ "
"vadesi."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, chieftain, when you tell me you don’t believe me you seem "
"like the blind man in the simile."

msgctxt "dn23:25.2"
msgid "Ko panetaṃ bhoto kassapassa āroceti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:25.3"
msgid "‘atthi devā tāvatiṃsā’ti vā, ‘evaṃdīghāyukā devā tāvatiṃsā’ti vā?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:25.4"
msgid "Na mayaṃ bhoto kassapassa saddahāma:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:25.5"
msgid "‘atthi devā tāvatiṃsā’ti vā ‘evaṃdīghāyukā devā tāvatiṃsā’ti vā”ti."
msgstr ""

# MS quotes are incorrect.
msgctxt "dn23:25.6"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, rājañña, evaṃ paro loko daṭṭhabbo, yathā tvaṃ maññasi iminā "
"maṃsacakkhunā."
msgstr ""
"You can’t see the other world the way you think, with the eye of the flesh."

msgctxt "dn23:25.7"
msgid ""
"Ye kho te, rājañña, samaṇabrāhmaṇā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni "
"paṭisevanti, te tattha appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharantā dibbacakkhuṃ "
"visodhenti."
msgstr ""
"There are ascetics and brahmins who live in the wilderness, frequenting "
"remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. Meditating diligent, keen, "
"and resolute, they purify the divine eye, the power of clairvoyance."

msgctxt "dn23:25.8"
msgid ""
"Te dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena imañceva lokaṃ passanti "
"parañca satte ca opapātike."
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see this world and "
"the other world, and sentient beings who are spontaneously reborn."

msgctxt "dn23:25.9"
msgid "Evañca kho, rājañña, paro loko daṭṭhabbo;"
msgstr "That’s how to see the other world,"

msgctxt "dn23:25.10"
msgid "na tveva yathā tvaṃ maññasi iminā maṃsacakkhunā."
msgstr "not how you think, with the eye of the flesh."

msgctxt "dn23:25.11"
msgid "Imināpi kho te, rājañña, pariyāyena evaṃ hotu:"
msgstr "By this method it ought to be proven that"

msgctxt "dn23:25.12"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there is an afterlife.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wp" id="wp12"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.330"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:26.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho evaṃ me ettha hoti:"
msgstr "“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I think that"

msgctxt "dn23:26.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

msgctxt "dn23:26.3"
msgid "“Atthi pana, rājañña, pariyāyo …"
msgstr "“Can you prove it?”"

msgctxt "dn23:26.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:26.5"
msgid "atthi, bho kassapa, pariyāyo …"
msgstr "“I can.”"

msgctxt "dn23:26.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:26.7"
msgid "yathā kathaṃ viya, rājaññā”ti?"
msgstr "“How, exactly, chieftain?”"

msgctxt "dn23:26.8"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bho kassapa, passāmi samaṇabrāhmaṇe sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme "
"jīvitukāme amaritukāme sukhakāme dukkhapaṭikūle."
msgstr ""
"“Well, I see ascetics and brahmins who are ethical, of good character, who "
"want to live and don’t want to die, who want to be happy and recoil from "
"pain."

msgctxt "dn23:26.9"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bho kassapa, evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "I think to myself:"

msgctxt "dn23:26.10"
msgid ""
"sace kho ime bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā evaṃ jāneyyuṃ:"
msgstr "‘If those ascetics and brahmins knew that"

msgctxt "dn23:26.11"
msgid "‘ito no matānaṃ seyyo bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "things were going to be better for them after death,"

msgctxt "dn23:26.12"
msgid ""
"Idānime bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā visaṃ vā khādeyyuṃ, "
"satthaṃ vā āhareyyuṃ, ubbandhitvā vā kālaṃ kareyyuṃ, papāte vā papateyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"they’d drink poison, slit their wrists, hang themselves, or throw themselves "
"off a cliff."

msgctxt "dn23:26.13"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho ime bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā na evaṃ "
"jānanti:"
msgstr "They mustn’t know that"

#. VAR:  attānaṃ na mārenti →  etthantare pāṭho syā1-3, kaṃ, pā1 potthakesu
msgctxt "dn23:26.14"
msgid ""
"‘ito no matānaṃ seyyo bhavissatī’ti, tasmā ime bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā jīvitukāmā amaritukāmā sukhakāmā dukkhapaṭikūlā "
"attānaṃ na mārenti."
msgstr ""
"things are going to be better for them after death. That’s why they are "
"ethical, of good character, wanting to live and not wanting to die, wanting "
"to be happy and recoiling from pain."

msgctxt "dn23:26.15"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "This is the method by which I prove that"

msgctxt "dn23:26.16"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:27.1"
msgid "2.6. Gabbhinīupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Pregnant Woman"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wp" id="wp13"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.331"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:28.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi."
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile."

msgctxt "dn23:28.2"
msgid "Upamāya midhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said. "

msgctxt "dn23:28.3"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, rājañña, aññatarassa brāhmaṇassa dve pajāpatiyo ahesuṃ."
msgstr "Once upon a time, a certain brahmin had two wives."

msgctxt "dn23:28.4"
msgid ""
"Ekissā putto ahosi dasavassuddesiko vā dvādasavassuddesiko vā, ekā gabbhinī "
"upavijaññā."
msgstr ""
"One had a son ten or twelve years of age, while the other was pregnant and "
"nearing her time."

msgctxt "dn23:28.5"
msgid "Atha kho so brāhmaṇo kālamakāsi."
msgstr "Then the brahmin passed away."

#. VAR: mātusapattiṃ → mātusapatiṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn23:28.6"
msgid "Atha kho so māṇavako mātusapattiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "So the youth said to his mother’s co-wife:"

msgctxt "dn23:28.7"
msgid ""
"‘yamidaṃ, bhoti, dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā, sabbaṃ taṃ "
"mayhaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Lady, all the wealth, grain, silver, and gold is mine,"

msgctxt "dn23:28.8"
msgid "natthi tuyhettha kiñci."
msgstr "and you get nothing."

# RD's translation of this is correct, MW's is wrong.
#. VAR: me → pitu me santako (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: niyyādehī’ti → niyyātehīti (bj) | nīyyātehīti (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:28.9"
msgid "Pitu me, bhoti, dāyajjaṃ niyyādehī’ti."
msgstr "Transfer to me my father’s inheritance.’"

msgctxt "dn23:28.10"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sā brāhmaṇī taṃ māṇavakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "But the brahmin lady said:"

msgctxt "dn23:28.11"
msgid "‘āgamehi tāva, tāta, yāva vijāyāmi."
msgstr "‘Wait, my dear, until I give birth."

msgctxt "dn23:28.12"
msgid "Sace kumārako bhavissati, tassapi ekadeso bhavissati;"
msgstr "If it’s a boy, one portion shall be his."

# RD and MW follow comm in saying she'll be his servant. But upabhunj means to enjoy, make use of, have sex with,, or get as reward. I think the salaciousness is deliberate.
#. VAR: opabhoggā → upabhoggā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:28.13"
msgid "sace kumārikā bhavissati, sāpi te opabhoggā bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "If it’s a girl, she will be your reward.’"

msgctxt "dn23:28.14"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho so māṇavako mātusapattiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "But for a second time,"

msgctxt "dn23:28.15"
msgid ""
"‘yamidaṃ, bhoti, dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā, sabbaṃ taṃ "
"mayhaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.16"
msgid "natthi tuyhettha kiñci."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.17"
msgid "Pitu me, bhoti, dāyajjaṃ niyyādehī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.18"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sā brāhmaṇī taṃ māṇavakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.19"
msgid "‘āgamehi tāva, tāta, yāva vijāyāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.20"
msgid "Sace kumārako bhavissati, tassapi ekadeso bhavissati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.21"
msgid "sace kumārikā bhavissati sāpi te opabhoggā bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.22"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho so māṇavako mātusapattiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"and a third time, the youth insisted that the entire inheritance must be his."

msgctxt "dn23:28.23"
msgid ""
"‘yamidaṃ, bhoti, dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā, sabbaṃ taṃ "
"mayhaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.24"
msgid "natthi tuyhettha kiñci."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:28.25"
msgid "Pitu me, bhoti, dāyajjaṃ niyyādehī’ti."
msgstr ""

# read opāṭesi
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.332"></a>
#. VAR: opādesi → opāṭesi (bj) | uppātesi (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:29.1"
msgid "Atha kho sā brāhmaṇī satthaṃ gahetvā ovarakaṃ pavisitvā udaraṃ opādesi:"
msgstr ""
"So the brahmin lady took a knife, went to her bedroom, and sliced open her "
"belly, thinking:"

# MW and RD follow PTS reading yava janami. But surely the phrase is meant to echo yava vijayami above. The phrase is not 100% coherent, which is understandable given the circumstances.
msgctxt "dn23:29.2"
msgid "‘yāva vijāyāmi yadi vā kumārako yadi vā kumārikā’ti."
msgstr "‘Until I give birth, whether it’s a boy or a girl!’"

msgctxt "dn23:29.3"
msgid "Sā attānañceva jīvitañca gabbhañca sāpateyyañca vināsesi."
msgstr ""
"She destroyed her own life and that of the embryo, as well as any wealth."

msgctxt "dn23:29.4"
msgid ""
"Yathā taṃ bālā abyattā anayabyasanaṃ āpannā ayoniso dāyajjaṃ gavesantī, "
"evameva kho tvaṃ, rājañña, bālo abyatto anayabyasanaṃ āpajjissasi ayoniso "
"paralokaṃ gavesanto;"
msgstr ""
"Being foolish and incompetent, she sought an inheritance in a irrational way "
"and came to ruin and disaster. In the same way, chieftain, being foolish and "
"incompetent, you’re seeking the other world in an irrational way and will "
"come to ruin and disaster,"

msgctxt "dn23:29.5"
msgid ""
"seyyathāpi sā brāhmaṇī bālā abyattā anayabyasanaṃ āpannā ayoniso dāyajjaṃ "
"gavesantī."
msgstr "just like that brahmin lady."

msgctxt "dn23:29.6"
msgid ""
"Na kho, rājañña, samaṇabrāhmaṇā sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā apakkaṃ paripācenti;"
msgstr "Good ascetics and brahmins don’t force what is unripe to ripen;"

msgctxt "dn23:29.7"
msgid "api ca paripākaṃ āgamenti."
msgstr "rather, they wait for it to ripen."

msgctxt "dn23:29.8"
msgid ""
"Paṇḍitānaṃ attho hi, rājañña, samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ sīlavantānaṃ "
"kalyāṇadhammānaṃ jīvitena."
msgstr "For the life of astute ascetics and brahmins is beneficial."

msgctxt "dn23:29.9"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā kho, rājañña, samaṇabrāhmaṇā sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā ciraṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ tiṭṭhanti tathā tathā bahuṃ puññaṃ pasavanti, bahujanahitāya "
"ca paṭipajjanti bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya "
"devamanussānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"So long as they remain, good ascetics and brahmins make much merit, and act "
"for the welfare and happiness of many people, for the benefit, welfare, and "
"happiness of gods and humans."

msgctxt "dn23:29.10"
msgid "Imināpi kho te, rājañña, pariyāyena evaṃ hotu:"
msgstr "By this method it ought to be proven that"

msgctxt "dn23:29.11"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there is an afterlife.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wp" id="wp14"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.333"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:30.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho evaṃ me ettha hoti:"
msgstr "“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I think that"

msgctxt "dn23:30.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

msgctxt "dn23:30.3"
msgid "“Atthi pana, rājañña, pariyāyo …"
msgstr "“Can you prove it?”"

msgctxt "dn23:30.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:30.5"
msgid "atthi, bho kassapa, pariyāyo …"
msgstr "“I can.”"

msgctxt "dn23:30.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:30.7"
msgid "yathā kathaṃ viya, rājaññā”ti?"
msgstr "“How, exactly, chieftain?”"

msgctxt "dn23:30.8"
msgid "“Idha me, bho kassapa, purisā coraṃ āgucāriṃ gahetvā dassenti:"
msgstr ""
"“Suppose they were to arrest a bandit, a criminal and present him to me, "
"saying:"

msgctxt "dn23:30.9"
msgid "‘ayaṃ te, bhante, coro āgucārī;"
msgstr "‘Sir, this is a bandit, a criminal."

msgctxt "dn23:30.10"
msgid "imassa yaṃ icchasi, taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti."
msgstr "Punish him as you will.’"

msgctxt "dn23:30.11"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "I say to them:"

# Note uddhanaṃ āropetvā is "on to a stove" not "in an oven".
msgctxt "dn23:30.12"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, imaṃ purisaṃ jīvantaṃyeva kumbhiyā pakkhipitvā mukhaṃ "
"pidahitvā allena cammena onandhitvā allāya mattikāya bahalāvalepanaṃ karitvā "
"uddhanaṃ āropetvā aggiṃ dethā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, sirs, place this man in a pot while he’s still alive. Close up "
"the mouth, bind it up with damp leather, and seal it with a thick coat of "
"damp clay. Then lift it up on a stove and light the fire.’"

msgctxt "dn23:30.13"
msgid ""
"Te me ‘sādhū’ti paṭissutvā taṃ purisaṃ jīvantaṃyeva kumbhiyā pakkhipitvā "
"mukhaṃ pidahitvā allena cammena onandhitvā allāya mattikāya bahalāvalepanaṃ "
"karitvā uddhanaṃ āropetvā aggiṃ denti."
msgstr "They agree, and do what I ask."

#. VAR: nillokema → vilokema (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:30.14"
msgid ""
"Yadā mayaṃ jānāma ‘kālaṅkato so puriso’ti, atha naṃ kumbhiṃ oropetvā "
"ubbhinditvā mukhaṃ vivaritvā saṇikaṃ nillokema:"
msgstr ""
"When we know that that man has died, we lift down the pot and break it open, "
"uncover the mouth, and slowly peek inside, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn23:30.15"
msgid "‘appeva nāmassa jīvaṃ nikkhamantaṃ passeyyāmā’ti."
msgstr "‘Hopefully we’ll see his soul escaping.’"

msgctxt "dn23:30.16"
msgid "Nevassa mayaṃ jīvaṃ nikkhamantaṃ passāma."
msgstr "But we don’t see his soul escaping."

msgctxt "dn23:30.17"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "This is how I prove that"

msgctxt "dn23:30.18"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:31.1"
msgid "2.7. Supinakaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Dream"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wp" id="wp15"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.334"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:32.1"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, rājañña, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi, yathā te khameyya, tathā naṃ "
"byākareyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, chieftain, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer "
"as you like."

msgctxt "dn23:32.2"
msgid ""
"Abhijānāsi no tvaṃ, rājañña, divā seyyaṃ upagato supinakaṃ passitā "
"ārāmarāmaṇeyyakaṃ vanarāmaṇeyyakaṃ bhūmirāmaṇeyyakaṃ "
"pokkharaṇīrāmaṇeyyakan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do you recall ever having a midday nap and seeing delightful parks, woods, "
"meadows, and lotus ponds in a dream?”"

msgctxt "dn23:32.3"
msgid ""
"“Abhijānāmahaṃ, bho kassapa, divāseyyaṃ upagato supinakaṃ passitā "
"ārāmarāmaṇeyyakaṃ vanarāmaṇeyyakaṃ bhūmirāmaṇeyyakaṃ "
"pokkharaṇīrāmaṇeyyakan”ti."
msgstr "“I do, sir.”"

# Readings and meaning here are obscure. Re velāsika, in the majority of similar cases (Ja547#10, thi-ap14#17, tha-ap411#4) the reading is celāpaka or something similar, so it seems that should accepted. This leaves the meaning unsolved; perhaps it should be "little bird". But given that it usually appears with khujja, it should probably have a similar meaning. See Cone. For kubja, Skt has "A young female servant of Kaṁsa, said to be deformed in three parts of her body. [Kṛiṣṇa and Balarāma, while proceeding to Mathurā, saw her on the high road carrying unguent to Kaṁsa. They asked her if she would give them some portion of it, and she gave as much as they wanted. Kṛiṣṇa, being very much pleased with her kindness, made her perfectly straight, and she began to appear a most beautiful woman.]" The Pali dictionaries are unhelpful here, as they merely state the obvious, that these are some kind of servant or attendant, but don't clarify why such people should act as attendants. Was this a genuine social phenomenon?
#. VAR: velāsikāpi → keḷāyikā pi (bj) | celāvikāpi (s1-3, km) | velāmikā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:32.4"
msgid ""
"“Rakkhanti taṃ tamhi samaye khujjāpi vāmanakāpi velāsikāpi komārikāpī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“At that time were you guarded by hunchbacks, dwarves, midgets, and "
"younglings?”"

msgctxt "dn23:32.5"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho kassapa, rakkhanti maṃ tamhi samaye khujjāpi vāmanakāpi "
"velāsikāpi komārikāpī”ti."
msgstr "“I was.”"

msgctxt "dn23:32.6"
msgid "“Api nu tā tuyhaṃ jīvaṃ passanti pavisantaṃ vā nikkhamantaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But did they see your soul entering or leaving?”"

msgctxt "dn23:32.7"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho kassapa”."
msgstr "“No they did not.”"

msgctxt "dn23:32.8"
msgid ""
"“Tā hi nāma, rājañña, tuyhaṃ jīvantassa jīvantiyo jīvaṃ na passissanti "
"pavisantaṃ vā nikkhamantaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“So if they couldn’t even see your soul entering or leaving while you weer "
"still alive,"

msgctxt "dn23:32.9"
msgid ""
"Kiṃ pana tvaṃ kālaṅkatassa jīvaṃ passissasi pavisantaṃ vā nikkhamantaṃ vā."
msgstr "how could you see the soul of a dead man?"

msgctxt "dn23:32.10"
msgid "Imināpi kho te, rājañña, pariyāyena evaṃ hotu:"
msgstr "By this method it ought to be proven that"

msgctxt "dn23:32.11"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr ""
"there is an afterlife, there are beings reborn spontaneously, and there is a "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wp" id="wp16"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:33.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho evaṃ me ettha hoti:"
msgstr "“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I think that"

msgctxt "dn23:33.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

msgctxt "dn23:33.3"
msgid "“Atthi pana, rājañña, pariyāyo …"
msgstr "“Can you prove it?”"

msgctxt "dn23:33.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:33.5"
msgid "“atthi, bho kassapa, pariyāyo …"
msgstr "“I can.”"

msgctxt "dn23:33.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:33.7"
msgid "yathā kathaṃ viya, rājaññā”ti?"
msgstr "“How, exactly, chieftain?”"

msgctxt "dn23:33.8"
msgid "“Idha me, bho kassapa, purisā coraṃ āgucāriṃ gahetvā dassenti:"
msgstr ""
"“Suppose they were to arrest a bandit, a criminal and present him to me, "
"saying:"

msgctxt "dn23:33.9"
msgid "‘ayaṃ te, bhante, coro āgucārī;"
msgstr "‘Sir, this is a bandit, a criminal."

msgctxt "dn23:33.10"
msgid "imassa yaṃ icchasi, taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti."
msgstr "Punish him as you will.’"

msgctxt "dn23:33.11"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "I say to them:"

msgctxt "dn23:33.12"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, imaṃ purisaṃ jīvantaṃyeva tulāya tuletvā jiyāya anassāsakaṃ "
"māretvā punadeva tulāya tulethā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, sirs, weigh this man with scales while he’s still alive. Then "
"strangle him with a bowstring, and when he’s dead, weigh him again.’"

msgctxt "dn23:33.13"
msgid ""
"Te me ‘sādhū’ti paṭissutvā taṃ purisaṃ jīvantaṃyeva tulāya tuletvā jiyāya "
"anassāsakaṃ māretvā punadeva tulāya tulenti."
msgstr "They agree, and do what I ask."

msgctxt "dn23:33.14"
msgid "Yadā so jīvati, tadā lahutaro ca hoti mudutaro ca kammaññataro ca."
msgstr "So long as they are alive, they’re lighter, softer, more flexible."

msgctxt "dn23:33.15"
msgid ""
"Yadā pana so kālaṅkato hoti tadā garutaro ca hoti patthinnataro ca "
"akammaññataro ca."
msgstr "But when they die they become heavier, stiffer, less flexible."

msgctxt "dn23:33.16"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "This is how I prove that"

msgctxt "dn23:33.17"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:34.1"
msgid "2.8. Santattaayoguḷaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Hot Iron Ball"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wp" id="wp17"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.335"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:35.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi."
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile."

msgctxt "dn23:35.2"
msgid "Upamāya midhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said."

msgctxt "dn23:35.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, rājañña, puriso divasaṃ santattaṃ ayoguḷaṃ ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ "
"sajotibhūtaṃ tulāya tuleyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to heat an iron ball all day until it was burning, "
"blazing, and glowing, and then they weigh it with scales."

msgctxt "dn23:35.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena sītaṃ nibbutaṃ tulāya tuleyya."
msgstr ""
"After some time, when it had cooled and become extinguished, they’d weigh it "
"again."

msgctxt "dn23:35.5"
msgid ""
"Kadā nu kho so ayoguḷo lahutaro vā hoti mudutaro vā kammaññataro vā, yadā vā "
"āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto, yadā vā sīto nibbuto”ti?"
msgstr ""
"When would that iron ball be lighter, softer, and more workable—when it’s "
"burning or when it’s cool?”"

msgctxt "dn23:35.6"
msgid ""
"“Yadā so, bho kassapa, ayoguḷo tejosahagato ca hoti vāyosahagato ca āditto "
"sampajjalito sajotibhūto, tadā lahutaro ca hoti mudutaro ca kammaññataro ca."
msgstr ""
"“So long as the iron ball is full of heat and air—burning, blazing, and "
"glowing—it’s lighter, softer, and more workable."

msgctxt "dn23:35.7"
msgid ""
"Yadā pana so ayoguḷo neva tejosahagato hoti na vāyosahagato sīto nibbuto, "
"tadā garutaro ca hoti patthinnataro ca akammaññataro cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"But when it lacks heat and air—cooled and extinguished—it’s heavier, "
"stiffer, and less workable.”"

msgctxt "dn23:35.8"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, rājañña, yadāyaṃ kāyo āyusahagato ca hoti usmāsahagato ca "
"viññāṇasahagato ca, tadā lahutaro ca hoti mudutaro ca kammaññataro ca."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, so long as this body is full of life and warmth and "
"consciousness it’s lighter, softer, and more flexible."

msgctxt "dn23:35.9"
msgid ""
"Yadā panāyaṃ kāyo neva āyusahagato hoti na usmāsahagato na viññāṇasahagato "
"tadā garutaro ca hoti patthinnataro ca akammaññataro ca."
msgstr ""
"But when it lacks life and warmth and consciousness it’s heavier, stiffer, "
"and less flexible."

msgctxt "dn23:35.10"
msgid "Imināpi kho te, rājañña, pariyāyena evaṃ hotu:"
msgstr "By this method it ought to be proven that"

msgctxt "dn23:35.11"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there is an afterlife.”"

