msgstr "I tell them to"

msgctxt "dn23:36.21"
msgid "‘tena hi, bho, imaṃ purisaṃ avakujjaṃ nipātetha …"
msgstr "lay him bent over, "

msgctxt "dn23:36.22"
msgid "passena nipātetha …"
msgstr "to lay him on his side,"

msgctxt "dn23:36.23"
msgid "dutiyena passena nipātetha …"
msgstr "to lay him on the other side;"

msgctxt "dn23:36.24"
msgid "uddhaṃ ṭhapetha …"
msgstr "to stand him upright,"

msgctxt "dn23:36.25"
msgid "omuddhakaṃ ṭhapetha …"
msgstr "to stand him upside down;"

msgctxt "dn23:36.26"
msgid "pāṇinā ākoṭetha …"
msgstr "to strike him with fists,"

msgctxt "dn23:36.27"
msgid "leḍḍunā ākoṭetha …"
msgstr "stones,"

msgctxt "dn23:36.28"
msgid "daṇḍena ākoṭetha …"
msgstr "rods,"

msgctxt "dn23:36.29"
msgid "satthena ākoṭetha …"
msgstr "and swords;"

msgctxt "dn23:36.30"
msgid ""
"odhunātha sandhunātha niddhunātha, appeva nāmassa jīvaṃ nikkhamantaṃ "
"passeyyāmā’ti."
msgstr "and to give him a good shaking in hope of seeing his soul escape.’"

msgctxt "dn23:36.31"
msgid "Te taṃ purisaṃ odhunanti sandhunanti niddhunanti."
msgstr "They do all these things."

msgctxt "dn23:36.32"
msgid "Nevassa mayaṃ jīvaṃ nikkhamantaṃ passāma."
msgstr "But we don’t see his soul escaping."

# Cp. AN 9.37, where this is more aptly describing a deep meditation. AS MW notes, this seems arbitrary here.
msgctxt "dn23:36.33"
msgid "Tassa tadeva cakkhu hoti te rūpā, tañcāyatanaṃ nappaṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"For him the eye itself is present, and so are those sights. Yet he does not "
"experience that sense-field."

msgctxt "dn23:36.34"
msgid "Tadeva sotaṃ hoti te saddā, tañcāyatanaṃ nappaṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"The ear itself is present, and so are those sounds. Yet he does not "
"experience that sense-field."

msgctxt "dn23:36.35"
msgid "Tadeva ghānaṃ hoti te gandhā, tañcāyatanaṃ nappaṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"The nose itself is present, and so are those smells. Yet he does not "
"experience that sense-field."

msgctxt "dn23:36.36"
msgid "Sāva jivhā hoti te rasā, tañcāyatanaṃ nappaṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"The tongue itself is present, and so are those tastes. Yet he does not "
"experience that sense-field."

msgctxt "dn23:36.37"
msgid "Sveva kāyo hoti te phoṭṭhabbā, tañcāyatanaṃ nappaṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"The body itself is present, and so are those touches. Yet he does not "
"experience that sense-field."

msgctxt "dn23:36.38"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "This is how I prove that"

msgctxt "dn23:36.39"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:37.1"
msgid "2.9. Saṅkhadhamaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Horn Blower"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wp" id="wp19"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.338"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:38.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi."
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile."

msgctxt "dn23:38.2"
msgid "Upamāya midhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said. "

msgctxt "dn23:38.3"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, rājañña, aññataro saṅkhadhamo saṅkhaṃ ādāya paccantimaṃ "
"janapadaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, a certain horn blower took his horn and traveled to a "
"borderland,"

msgctxt "dn23:38.4"
msgid "So yena aññataro gāmo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "where he went to a certain village."

msgctxt "dn23:38.5"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā majjhe gāmassa ṭhito tikkhattuṃ saṅkhaṃ upalāpetvā saṅkhaṃ "
"bhūmiyaṃ nikkhipitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Standing in the middle of the village, he sounded his horn three times, then "
"placed it on the ground and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "dn23:38.6"
msgid "Atha kho, rājañña, tesaṃ paccantajanapadānaṃ manussānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the people of the borderland thought:"

#. VAR: ambho kassa nu kho → etadahosi \
msgctxt "dn23:38.7"
msgid ""
"‘ambho kassa nu kho eso saddo evaṃrajanīyo evaṃkamanīyo evaṃmadanīyo "
"evambandhanīyo evaṃmucchanīyo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘What is making this sound, so arousing, desirable, intoxicating, "
"stupefying, and captivating?’"

msgctxt "dn23:38.8"
msgid "Sannipatitvā taṃ saṅkhadhamaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "They gathered around the horn blower and said:"

msgctxt "dn23:38.9"
msgid ""
"‘ambho, kassa nu kho eso saddo evaṃrajanīyo evaṃkamanīyo evaṃmadanīyo "
"evambandhanīyo evaṃmucchanīyo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, what is making this sound, so arousing, desirable, intoxicating, "
"stupefying, and captivating?’"

msgctxt "dn23:38.10"
msgid ""
"‘Eso kho, bho, saṅkho nāma yasseso saddo evaṃrajanīyo evaṃkamanīyo "
"evaṃmadanīyo evambandhanīyo evaṃmucchanīyo’ti."
msgstr "‘The sound is made by this, which is called a horn.’"

msgctxt "dn23:38.11"
msgid "Te taṃ saṅkhaṃ uttānaṃ nipātesuṃ:"
msgstr "They laid that horn on its back, saying:"

msgctxt "dn23:38.12"
msgid "‘vadehi, bho saṅkha, vadehi, bho saṅkhā’ti."
msgstr "‘Speak, good horn! Speak, good horn!’"

msgctxt "dn23:38.13"
msgid "Neva so saṅkho saddamakāsi."
msgstr "But still the horn made no sound."

msgctxt "dn23:38.14"
msgid ""
"Te taṃ saṅkhaṃ avakujjaṃ nipātesuṃ, passena nipātesuṃ, dutiyena passena "
"nipātesuṃ, uddhaṃ ṭhapesuṃ, omuddhakaṃ ṭhapesuṃ, pāṇinā ākoṭesuṃ, leḍḍunā "
"ākoṭesuṃ, daṇḍena ākoṭesuṃ, satthena ākoṭesuṃ, odhuniṃsu sandhuniṃsu "
"niddhuniṃsu:"
msgstr ""
"Then they lay the horn bent over, they lay it on its side, they lay it on "
"its other side, they stood it upright, they stood it upside down, they "
"struck it with fists, stones, rods, and swords, and they gave it a good "
"shake."

msgctxt "dn23:38.15"
msgid "‘vadehi, bho saṅkha, vadehi, bho saṅkhā’ti."
msgstr "‘Speak, good horn! Speak, good horn!’"

msgctxt "dn23:38.16"
msgid "Neva so saṅkho saddamakāsi."
msgstr "But still the horn made no sound."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:39.1"
msgid "Atha kho, rājañña, tassa saṅkhadhamassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "So the horn blower thought:"

msgctxt "dn23:39.2"
msgid ""
"‘yāva bālā ime paccantajanapadā manussā, kathañhi nāma ayoniso saṅkhasaddaṃ "
"gavesissantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How foolish are these borderland folk! For how can they seek the sound of a "
"horn so irrationally!’"

msgctxt "dn23:39.3"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pekkhamānānaṃ saṅkhaṃ gahetvā tikkhattuṃ saṅkhaṃ upalāpetvā saṅkhaṃ "
"ādāya pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"And as they looked on, he picked up the horn, sounded it three times, and "
"took it away with him."

msgctxt "dn23:39.4"
msgid "Atha kho, rājañña, tesaṃ paccantajanapadānaṃ manussānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the people of the borderland thought:"

#. VAR: vāyāmasahagato → vāyosahagato (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:39.5"
msgid ""
"‘yadā kira, bho, ayaṃ saṅkho nāma purisasahagato ca hoti vāyāmasahagato ca "
"vāyusahagato ca, tadāyaṃ saṅkho saddaṃ karoti, yadā panāyaṃ saṅkho neva "
"purisasahagato hoti na vāyāmasahagato na vāyusahagato, nāyaṃ saṅkho saddaṃ "
"karotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘So, it seems, when what is called a horn is accompanied by a person, "
"effort, and wind, it makes a sound. But when these things are absent it "
"makes no sound.’"

msgctxt "dn23:39.6"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, rājañña, yadāyaṃ kāyo āyusahagato ca hoti usmāsahagato ca "
"viññāṇasahagato ca, tadā abhikkamatipi paṭikkamatipi tiṭṭhatipi nisīdatipi "
"seyyampi kappeti, cakkhunāpi rūpaṃ passati, sotenapi saddaṃ suṇāti, "
"ghānenapi gandhaṃ ghāyati, jivhāyapi rasaṃ sāyati, kāyenapi phoṭṭhabbaṃ "
"phusati, manasāpi dhammaṃ vijānāti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, so long as this body is full of life and warmth and "
"consciousness it walks back and forth, stands, sits and lies down. It sees "
"sights with the eye, hears sounds with the ear, smells odors with the nose, "
"tastes flavors with the tongue, feels touches with the body, and knows "
"thoughts with the mind."

msgctxt "dn23:39.7"
msgid ""
"Yadā panāyaṃ kāyo neva āyusahagato hoti, na usmāsahagato, na "
"viññāṇasahagato, tadā neva abhikkamati na paṭikkamati na tiṭṭhati na "
"nisīdati na seyyaṃ kappeti, cakkhunāpi rūpaṃ na passati, sotenapi saddaṃ na "
"suṇāti, ghānenapi gandhaṃ na ghāyati, jivhāyapi rasaṃ na sāyati, kāyenapi "
"phoṭṭhabbaṃ na phusati, manasāpi dhammaṃ na vijānāti."
msgstr ""
"But when it lacks life and warmth and consciousness it does none of these "
"things."

msgctxt "dn23:39.8"
msgid "Imināpi kho te, rājañña, pariyāyena evaṃ hotu:"
msgstr "By this method it ought to be proven that"

msgctxt "dn23:39.9"
msgid ""
"‘itipi atthi paro loko, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there is an afterlife.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wp" id="wp20"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.339"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:40.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho evaṃ me ettha hoti:"
msgstr "“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I think that"

msgctxt "dn23:40.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

msgctxt "dn23:40.3"
msgid "“Atthi pana, rājañña, pariyāyo …"
msgstr "“Can you prove it?”"

msgctxt "dn23:40.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:40.5"
msgid "atthi, bho kassapa, pariyāyo …"
msgstr "“I can.”"

msgctxt "dn23:40.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:40.7"
msgid "yathā kathaṃ viya, rājaññā”ti?"
msgstr "“How, exactly, chieftain?”"

msgctxt "dn23:40.8"
msgid "“Idha me, bho kassapa, purisā coraṃ āgucāriṃ gahetvā dassenti:"
msgstr ""
"“Suppose they were to arrest a bandit, a criminal and present him to me, "
"saying:"

msgctxt "dn23:40.9"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ te, bhante, coro āgucārī, imassa yaṃ icchasi, taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti."
msgstr "‘Sir, this is a bandit, a criminal. Punish him as you will.’"

msgctxt "dn23:40.10"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "I say to them:"

msgctxt "dn23:40.11"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, imassa purisassa chaviṃ chindatha, appeva nāmassa jīvaṃ "
"passeyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, sirs, cut open this man’s outer skin. Hopefully we might see his "
"soul.’"

msgctxt "dn23:40.12"
msgid "Te tassa purisassa chaviṃ chindanti."
msgstr "They cut open his outer skin,"

msgctxt "dn23:40.13"
msgid "Nevassa mayaṃ jīvaṃ passāma."
msgstr "but we see no soul."

msgctxt "dn23:40.14"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "I say to them:"

msgctxt "dn23:40.15"
msgid ""
"‘tena hi, bho, imassa purisassa cammaṃ chindatha, maṃsaṃ chindatha, nhāruṃ "
"chindatha, aṭṭhiṃ chindatha, aṭṭhimiñjaṃ chindatha, appeva nāmassa jīvaṃ "
"passeyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, sirs, cut open his inner skin, flesh, sinews, bones, or marrow. "
"Hopefully we’ll see his soul.’"

msgctxt "dn23:40.16"
msgid ""
"Te tassa purisassa aṭṭhimiñjaṃ chindanti, nevassa mayaṃ jīvaṃ passeyyāma."
msgstr "They do so, but we see no soul."

msgctxt "dn23:40.17"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bho kassapa, pariyāyo, yena me pariyāyena evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "This is how I prove that"

msgctxt "dn23:40.18"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti."
msgstr "there’s no afterlife.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:41.1"
msgid "2.10. Aggikajaṭilaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Fire-Worshiping Matted-Hair Ascetic"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wp" id="wp21"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.340"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:42.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi."
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile."

msgctxt "dn23:42.2"
msgid "Upamāya midhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said. "

#. VAR: sammati → vasati (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:42.3"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, rājañña, aññataro aggiko jaṭilo araññāyatane paṇṇakuṭiyā "
"sammati."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, a certain fire-worshiping matted-hair ascetic settled in a "
"leaf hut in a wilderness region."

#. VAR: sattho → satthavāso (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: janapade sattho → janapado satthavāso (s1-3, km) | janapadapadeso
#. (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:42.4"
msgid "Atha kho, rājañña, aññataro janapade sattho vuṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "Then a caravan came out from a certain country."

msgctxt "dn23:42.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so sattho tassa aggikassa jaṭilassa assamassa sāmantā ekarattiṃ "
"vasitvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"It stayed for one night not far from that ascetic’s hermitage, and then "
"moved on."

msgctxt "dn23:42.6"
msgid "Atha kho, rājañña, tassa aggikassa jaṭilassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "The ascetic thought:"

msgctxt "dn23:42.7"
msgid ""
"‘yannūnāhaṃ yena so satthavāso tenupasaṅkameyyaṃ, appeva nāmettha kiñci "
"upakaraṇaṃ adhigaccheyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Why don’t I go to that caravan’s campsite? Hopefully I’ll find something "
"useful there.’"

msgctxt "dn23:42.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so aggiko jaṭilo kālasseva vuṭṭhāya yena so satthavāso "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "So he went,"

msgctxt "dn23:42.9"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā addasa tasmiṃ satthavāse daharaṃ kumāraṃ mandaṃ uttānaseyyakaṃ "
"chaḍḍitaṃ."
msgstr "and he saw a young baby boy abandoned there."

msgctxt "dn23:42.10"
msgid "Disvānassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "When he saw this he thought:"

msgctxt "dn23:42.11"
msgid ""
"‘na kho me taṃ patirūpaṃ yaṃ me pekkhamānassa manussabhūto kālaṃkareyya;"
msgstr "‘It’s not proper for me to look on while a human being dies."

msgctxt "dn23:42.12"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ dārakaṃ assamaṃ netvā āpādeyyaṃ poseyyaṃ vaḍḍheyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I bring this boy back to my hermitage, nurse him, nourish him, and "
"raise him?’"

msgctxt "dn23:42.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so aggiko jaṭilo taṃ dārakaṃ assamaṃ netvā āpādesi posesi vaḍḍhesi."
msgstr "So that’s what he does."

#. VAR: hoti → ahosi (?)
msgctxt "dn23:42.14"
msgid ""
"Yadā so dārako dasavassuddesiko vā hoti dvādasavassuddesiko vā, atha kho "
"tassa aggikassa jaṭilassa janapade kañcideva karaṇīyaṃ uppajji."
msgstr ""
"When the boy was ten or twelve years old, the ascetic had some business come "
"up in the country."

msgctxt "dn23:42.15"
msgid "Atha kho so aggiko jaṭilo taṃ dārakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "So he said to the boy:"

#. VAR: janapadaṃ → nagaraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn23:42.16"
msgid "‘icchāmahaṃ, tāta, janapadaṃ gantuṃ;"
msgstr "‘My dear, I wish to go to the country."

msgctxt "dn23:42.17"
msgid "aggiṃ, tāta, paricareyyāsi."
msgstr "Serve the sacred flame."

msgctxt "dn23:42.18"
msgid "Mā ca te aggi nibbāyi."
msgstr "Do not extinguish it."

msgctxt "dn23:42.19"
msgid ""
"Sace ca te aggi nibbāyeyya, ayaṃ vāsī imāni kaṭṭhāni idaṃ araṇisahitaṃ, "
"aggiṃ nibbattetvā aggiṃ paricareyyāsī’ti."
msgstr ""
"But if you should extinguish it, here is the hatchet, the firewood, and the "
"bundle of drill-sticks. Light the fire and serve it.’"

msgctxt "dn23:42.20"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so aggiko jaṭilo taṃ dārakaṃ evaṃ anusāsitvā janapadaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "And having instructed the boy, the ascetic went to the country."

msgctxt "dn23:42.21"
msgid "Tassa khiḍḍāpasutassa aggi nibbāyi."
msgstr "But the boy was so intent on his play, the fire went out."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.341"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:43.1"
msgid "Atha kho tassa dārakassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "He thought:"

msgctxt "dn23:43.2"
msgid "‘pitā kho maṃ evaṃ avaca:"
msgstr "‘My father told me to serve the sacred flame."

msgctxt "dn23:43.3"
msgid "“aggiṃ, tāta, paricareyyāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:43.4"
msgid "Mā ca te aggi nibbāyi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:43.5"
msgid ""
"Sace ca te aggi nibbāyeyya, ayaṃ vāsī imāni kaṭṭhāni idaṃ araṇisahitaṃ, "
"aggiṃ nibbattetvā aggiṃ paricareyyāsī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:43.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ aggiṃ nibbattetvā aggiṃ paricareyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I light it again and serve it?’"

msgctxt "dn23:43.7"
msgid "Atha kho so dārako araṇisahitaṃ vāsiyā tacchi:"
msgstr "So he chopped the bundle of drill-sticks with the hatchet, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn23:43.8"
msgid "‘appeva nāma aggiṃ adhigaccheyyan’ti."
msgstr "‘Hopefully I’ll get a fire!’"

msgctxt "dn23:43.9"
msgid "Neva so aggiṃ adhigacchi."
msgstr "But he still got no fire."

#. VAR: opuni → opuṇi (bj) | ophuni (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: satadhā → vīsatidhā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:43.10"
msgid ""
"Araṇisahitaṃ dvidhā phālesi, tidhā phālesi, catudhā phālesi, pañcadhā "
"phālesi, dasadhā phālesi, satadhā phālesi, sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ akāsi, "
"sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ karitvā udukkhale koṭṭesi, udukkhale koṭṭetvā mahāvāte "
"opuni:"
msgstr ""
"He split the bundle of drill-sticks into two, three, four, five, ten, or a "
"hundred parts. He chopped them into splinters, pounded them in a mortar, and "
"swept them away in a strong wind, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn23:43.11"
msgid "‘appeva nāma aggiṃ adhigaccheyyan’ti."
msgstr "‘Hopefully I’ll get a fire!’"

msgctxt "dn23:43.12"
msgid "Neva so aggiṃ adhigacchi."
msgstr "But he still got no fire."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.342"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:44.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so aggiko jaṭilo janapade taṃ karaṇīyaṃ tīretvā yena sako assamo "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then the matted-hair ascetic, having concluded his business in the country, "
"returned to his own hermitage,"

msgctxt "dn23:44.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ dārakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to the boy:"

msgctxt "dn23:44.3"
msgid "‘kacci te, tāta, aggi na nibbuto’ti?"
msgstr "‘I trust, my dear, that the fire didn’t go out?’"

msgctxt "dn23:44.4"
msgid "‘Idha me, tāta, khiḍḍāpasutassa aggi nibbāyi."
msgstr "And the boy told him what had happened."

msgctxt "dn23:44.5"
msgid "Tassa me etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.6"
msgid "“pitā kho maṃ evaṃ avaca aggiṃ, tāta, paricareyyāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.7"
msgid "Mā ca te, tāta, aggi nibbāyi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.8"
msgid ""
"Sace ca te aggi nibbāyeyya, ayaṃ vāsī imāni kaṭṭhāni idaṃ araṇisahitaṃ, "
"aggiṃ nibbattetvā aggiṃ paricareyyāsīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.9"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ aggiṃ nibbattetvā aggiṃ paricareyyan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.10"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, tāta, araṇisahitaṃ vāsiyā tacchiṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.11"
msgid "“appeva nāma aggiṃ adhigaccheyyan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.12"
msgid "Nevāhaṃ aggiṃ adhigacchiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.13"
msgid ""
"Araṇisahitaṃ dvidhā phālesiṃ, tidhā phālesiṃ, catudhā phālesiṃ, pañcadhā "
"phālesiṃ, dasadhā phālesiṃ, satadhā phālesiṃ, sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ akāsiṃ, "
"sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ karitvā udukkhale koṭṭesiṃ, udukkhale koṭṭetvā mahāvāte "
"opuniṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.14"
msgid "“appeva nāma aggiṃ adhigaccheyyan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.15"
msgid "Nevāhaṃ aggiṃ adhigacchin’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:44.16"
msgid "Atha kho tassa aggikassa jaṭilassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the ascetic thought:"

msgctxt "dn23:44.17"
msgid ""
"‘yāva bālo ayaṃ dārako abyatto, kathañhi nāma ayoniso aggiṃ gavesissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How foolish is this boy, how incompetent! For how can he seek a fire so "
"irrationally!’"

msgctxt "dn23:44.18"
msgid ""
"Tassa pekkhamānassa araṇisahitaṃ gahetvā aggiṃ nibbattetvā taṃ dārakaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"So while the boy looked on, he took a bundle of fire-sticks, lit the fire, "
"and said:"

msgctxt "dn23:44.19"
msgid "‘evaṃ kho, tāta, aggi nibbattetabbo."
msgstr "‘Dear boy, this is how to light a fire."

msgctxt "dn23:44.20"
msgid "Na tveva yathā tvaṃ bālo abyatto ayoniso aggiṃ gavesī’ti."
msgstr "Not the foolish and incompetent way you sought it so irrationally.’"

# Note that verb tenses in this passage very in editions: I translate according to the sense.
msgctxt "dn23:44.21"
msgid "Evameva kho tvaṃ, rājañña, bālo abyatto ayoniso paralokaṃ gavesissasi."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, chieftain, being foolish and incompetent, you seek the "
"other world irrationally."

msgctxt "dn23:44.22"
msgid ""
"Paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ, paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, "
"pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ, mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Let go of this harmful misconception, chieftain, let go of it! Don’t create "
"lasting harm and suffering for yourself!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="wp" id="wp22"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:45.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho nevāhaṃ sakkomi idaṃ pāpakaṃ "
"diṭṭhigataṃ paṭinissajjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I’m not able to let go of that "
"harmful misconception."

msgctxt "dn23:45.2"
msgid "Rājāpi maṃ pasenadi kosalo jānāti tirorājānopi:"
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala knows my views, and so do foreign kings."

msgctxt "dn23:45.3"
msgid "‘pāyāsi rājañño evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhī:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:45.4"
msgid ""
"“itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko”’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:45.5"
msgid ""
"Sacāhaṃ, bho kassapa, idaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ paṭinissajjissāmi, "
"bhavissanti me vattāro:"
msgstr "If I let go of this harmful misconception, people will say:"

msgctxt "dn23:45.6"
msgid "‘yāva bālo pāyāsi rājañño abyatto duggahitagāhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How foolish is the chieftain Pāyāsi, how incompetent, that he should hold "
"on to a mistake!’"

msgctxt "dn23:45.7"
msgid ""
"Kopenapi naṃ harissāmi, makkhenapi naṃ harissāmi, palāsenapi naṃ "
"harissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I shall carry on with this view out of anger, contempt, and spite!”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:46.1"
msgid "2.11. Dvesatthavāhaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Two Caravan Leaders"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="wp" id="wp23"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.343"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:47.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi."
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile."

msgctxt "dn23:47.2"
msgid "Upamāya midhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said. "

msgctxt "dn23:47.3"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, rājañña, mahāsakaṭasattho sakaṭasahassaṃ puratthimā janapadā "
"pacchimaṃ janapadaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time a large caravan of a thousand wagons traveled from a "
"country in the east to the west."

msgctxt "dn23:47.4"
msgid ""
"So yena yena gacchi, khippaṃyeva pariyādiyati tiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ haritakapaṇṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Wherever they went they quickly used up the grass, wood, and water, and the "
"green foliage."

msgctxt "dn23:47.5"
msgid ""
"Tasmiṃ kho pana satthe dve satthavāhā ahesuṃ eko pañcannaṃ sakaṭasatānaṃ, "
"eko pañcannaṃ sakaṭasatānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now, that caravan had two leaders, each in charge of five hundred wagons."

msgctxt "dn23:47.6"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ satthavāhānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "They thought:"

msgctxt "dn23:47.7"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho mahāsakaṭasattho sakaṭasahassaṃ;"
msgstr "‘This is a large caravan of a thousand wagons."

msgctxt "dn23:47.8"
msgid ""
"te mayaṃ yena yena gacchāma, khippameva pariyādiyati tiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ "
"haritakapaṇṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Wherever we go we quickly use up the grass, wood, and water, and the green "
"foliage."

msgctxt "dn23:47.9"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ imaṃ satthaṃ dvidhā vibhajeyyāma—"
msgstr "Why don’t we split the caravan in two halves?’"

msgctxt "dn23:47.10"
msgid "ekato pañca sakaṭasatāni ekato pañca sakaṭasatānī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: vibhajiṃsu → vibhajesuṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn23:47.11"
msgid ""
"Te taṃ satthaṃ dvidhā vibhajiṃsu ekato pañca sakaṭasatāni, ekato pañca "
"sakaṭasatāni."
msgstr "So that’s what they did."

#. VAR: payāpesi → pāyāpesi (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:47.12"
msgid ""
"Eko satthavāho bahuṃ tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca udakañca āropetvā satthaṃ payāpesi."
msgstr ""
"One caravan leader, having prepared much grass, wood, and water, started the "
"caravan."

# Read gadrabharathena
#. VAR: lohitakkhaṃ → lohitakkhiṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:47.13"
msgid ""
"Dvīhatīhapayāto kho pana so sattho addasa purisaṃ kāḷaṃ lohitakkhaṃ "
"sannaddhakalāpaṃ kumudamāliṃ allavatthaṃ allakesaṃ kaddamamakkhitehi cakkehi "
"bhadrena rathena paṭipathaṃ āgacchantaṃ, disvā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"After two or three days’ journey he saw a dark man with red eyes coming the "
"other way in a donkey cart with muddy wheels. He was armored with a quiver "
"and wreathed with yellow lotus, his clothes and hair all wet. Seeing him, he "
"said:"

msgctxt "dn23:47.14"
msgid "‘kuto, bho, āgacchasī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Sir, where do you come from?’"

msgctxt "dn23:47.15"
msgid "‘Amukamhā janapadā’ti."
msgstr "‘From such and such a country.’"

msgctxt "dn23:47.16"
msgid "‘Kuhiṃ gamissasī’ti?"
msgstr "‘And where are you going?’"

msgctxt "dn23:47.17"
msgid "‘Amukaṃ nāma janapadan’ti."
msgstr "‘To the country named so and so.’"

msgctxt "dn23:47.18"
msgid "‘Kacci, bho, purato kantāre mahāmegho abhippavuṭṭho’ti?"
msgstr "‘But has there been much rain in the desert up ahead?’"

msgctxt "dn23:47.19"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bho, purato kantāre mahāmegho abhippavuṭṭho, āsittodakāni vaṭumāni, "
"bahu tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca udakañca."
msgstr ""
"‘Indeed there has, sir. The paths are sprinkled with water, and there is "
"much grass, wood, and water."

msgctxt "dn23:47.20"
msgid ""
"Chaḍḍetha, bho, purāṇāni tiṇāni kaṭṭhāni udakāni, lahubhārehi sakaṭehi "
"sīghaṃ sīghaṃ gacchatha, mā yoggāni kilamitthā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Toss out your grass, wood, and water. Your wagons will move swiftly when "
"lightly-laden, so don’t tire your draught teams.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:48.1"
msgid "Atha kho so satthavāho satthike āmantesi:"
msgstr "So the caravan leader addressed his drivers:"

msgctxt "dn23:48.2"
msgid "‘ayaṃ, bho, puriso evamāha:"
msgstr "‘This man says that"

msgctxt "dn23:48.3"
msgid ""
"“purato kantāre mahāmegho abhippavuṭṭho, āsittodakāni vaṭumāni, bahu tiṇañca "
"kaṭṭhañca udakañca."
msgstr "there has been much rain in the desert up ahead."

msgctxt "dn23:48.4"
msgid ""
"Chaḍḍetha, bho, purāṇāni tiṇāni kaṭṭhāni udakāni, lahubhārehi sakaṭehi "
"sīghaṃ sīghaṃ gacchatha, mā yoggāni kilamitthā”ti."
msgstr ""
"He advises us to toss out the grass, wood, and water. The wagons will move "
"swiftly when lightly-laden, and won’t tire our draught teams."

msgctxt "dn23:48.5"
msgid ""
"Chaḍḍetha, bho, purāṇāni tiṇāni kaṭṭhāni udakāni, lahubhārehi sakaṭehi "
"satthaṃ payāpethā’ti."
msgstr ""
"So let’s toss out the grass, wood, and water and restart the caravan with "
"lightly-laden wagons.’"

msgctxt "dn23:48.6"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bho’ti kho te satthikā tassa satthavāhassa paṭissutvā chaḍḍetvā "
"purāṇāni tiṇāni kaṭṭhāni udakāni lahubhārehi sakaṭehi satthaṃ payāpesuṃ."
msgstr "‘Yes, sir,’ the drivers replied, and that’s what they did."

msgctxt "dn23:48.7"
msgid "Te paṭhamepi satthavāse na addasaṃsu tiṇaṃ vā kaṭṭhaṃ vā udakaṃ vā."
msgstr "But in the caravan’s first campsite they saw no grass, wood, or water."

msgctxt "dn23:48.8"
msgid "Dutiyepi satthavāse …"
msgstr "And in the second,"

msgctxt "dn23:48.9"
msgid "tatiyepi satthavāse …"
msgstr "third,"

msgctxt "dn23:48.10"
msgid "catutthepi satthavāse …"
msgstr "fourth,"

msgctxt "dn23:48.11"
msgid "pañcamepi satthavāse …"
msgstr "fifth,"

msgctxt "dn23:48.12"
msgid "chaṭṭhepi satthavāse …"
msgstr "sixth,"

msgctxt "dn23:48.13"
msgid "sattamepi satthavāse na addasaṃsu tiṇaṃ vā kaṭṭhaṃ vā udakaṃ vā."
msgstr "and seventh campsites they saw no grass, wood, or water."

msgctxt "dn23:48.14"
msgid "Sabbeva anayabyasanaṃ āpajjiṃsu."
msgstr "And all came to ruin and disaster."

msgctxt "dn23:48.15"
msgid ""
"Ye ca tasmiṃ satthe ahesuṃ manussā vā pasū vā, sabbe so yakkho amanusso "
"bhakkhesi."
msgstr ""
"And the men and beasts in that caravan were all devoured by that non-human "
"spirit."

msgctxt "dn23:48.16"
msgid "Aṭṭhikāneva sesāni."
msgstr "Only their bones remained."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.345"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:49.1"
msgid "Yadā aññāsi dutiyo satthavāho:"
msgstr "Now, when the second caravan leader knew that"

msgctxt "dn23:49.2"
msgid ""
"‘bahunikkhanto kho, bho, dāni so sattho’ti bahuṃ tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca udakañca "
"āropetvā satthaṃ payāpesi."
msgstr ""
"the first caravan was well underway, he prepared much grass, wood, and water "
"and started the caravan."

msgctxt "dn23:49.3"
msgid ""
"Dvīhatīhapayāto kho pana so sattho addasa purisaṃ kāḷaṃ lohitakkhaṃ "
"sannaddhakalāpaṃ kumudamāliṃ allavatthaṃ allakesaṃ kaddamamakkhitehi cakkehi "
"bhadrena rathena paṭipathaṃ āgacchantaṃ, disvā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"After two or three days’ journey he saw a dark man with red eyes coming the "
"other way in a donkey cart with muddy wheels. He was armored with a quiver "
"and wreathed with yellow lotus, his clothes and hair all wet. Seeing him, he "
"said:"

msgctxt "dn23:49.4"
msgid "‘kuto, bho, āgacchasī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Sir, where do you come from?’"

msgctxt "dn23:49.5"
msgid "‘Amukamhā janapadā’ti."
msgstr "‘From such and such a country.’"

