msgctxt "dn23:61.1"
msgid "2.14. Sāṇabhārikaupamā"
msgstr "The Simile of the Man Who Carried Hemp"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="wp" id="wp29"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.350"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:62.1"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi, upamāya midhekacce viññū purisā "
"bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile. For by means of a simile "
"some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said. "

msgctxt "dn23:62.2"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, rājañña, aññataro janapado vuṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "Once upon a time, the inhabitants of a certain country emigrated."

msgctxt "dn23:62.3"
msgid "Atha kho sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then one friend said to another:"

msgctxt "dn23:62.4"
msgid ""
"‘āyāma, samma, yena so janapado tenupasaṅkamissāma, appeva nāmettha kiñci "
"dhanaṃ adhigaccheyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Come, my friend, let’s go to that country. Hopefully we’ll get some riches "
"there!’"

msgctxt "dn23:62.5"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, sammā’ti kho sahāyako sahāyakassa paccassosi."
msgstr "‘Yes, my friend,’ the other replied."

# Comm: "Gāmapaṭṭanti vuṭṭhitagāmapadeso vuccati. ‘‘Gāmapada’’ntipi pāṭho, ayamevattho"
#. VAR: gāmapaṭṭaṃ → gāmapatthaṃ (bj) | gāmapajjaṃ (s1-3) | gāmapaddhanaṃ
#. (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:62.6"
msgid ""
"Te yena so janapado, yena aññataraṃ gāmapaṭṭaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, tattha "
"addasaṃsu pahūtaṃ sāṇaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"They went to that country, and to a certain place in a village. There they "
"saw a pile of abandoned sunn hemp. Seeing it, one friend said to the other:"

msgctxt "dn23:62.7"
msgid ""
"‘idaṃ kho, samma, pahūtaṃ sāṇaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, tena hi, samma, tvañca sāṇabhāraṃ "
"bandha, ahañca sāṇabhāraṃ bandhissāmi, ubho sāṇabhāraṃ ādāya gamissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is a pile of abandoned sunn hemp. Well then, my friend, you make up a "
"bundle of hemp, and I’ll make one too. Let’s both take a bundle of hemp and "
"go on.’"

msgctxt "dn23:62.8"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, sammā’ti kho sahāyako sahāyakassa paṭissutvā sāṇabhāraṃ bandhitvā te "
"ubho sāṇabhāraṃ ādāya yena aññataraṃ gāmapaṭṭaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"‘Yes, my friend,’ he said. Carrying their bundles of hemp they went to "
"another place in the village."

msgctxt "dn23:62.9"
msgid ""
"Tattha addasaṃsu pahūtaṃ sāṇasuttaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā sahāyako sahāyakaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"There they saw much sunn hemp thread abandoned. Seeing it, one friend said "
"to the other:"

msgctxt "dn23:62.10"
msgid ""
"‘yassa kho, samma, atthāya iccheyyāma sāṇaṃ, idaṃ pahūtaṃ sāṇasuttaṃ "
"chaḍḍitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘This pile of abandoned sunn hemp thread is just what we wanted the hemp for!"

msgctxt "dn23:62.11"
msgid ""
"Tena hi, samma, tvañca sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍehi, ahañca sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍessāmi, "
"ubho sāṇasuttabhāraṃ ādāya gamissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Well then, my friend, let’s abandon our bundles of hemp, and both take a "
"bundle of hemp thread and go on.’"

# The sunk cost fallacy!
msgctxt "dn23:62.12"
msgid ""
"‘Ayaṃ kho me, samma, sāṇabhāro dūrābhato ca susannaddho ca, alaṃ me, tvaṃ "
"pajānāhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve already carried this bundle of hemp a long way, and it’s well tied up. "
"It’s good enough for me, you understand.’"

msgctxt "dn23:62.13"
msgid "Atha kho so sahāyako sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍetvā sāṇasuttabhāraṃ ādiyi."
msgstr ""
"So one friend abandoned their bundle of hemp and picked up a bundle of hemp "
"thread."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:63.1"
msgid "Te yena aññataraṃ gāmapaṭṭaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu."
msgstr "They went to another place in the village."

msgctxt "dn23:63.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha addasaṃsu pahūtā sāṇiyo chaḍḍitā, disvā sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"There they saw much sunn hemp cloth abandoned. Seeing it, one friend said to "
"the other:"

msgctxt "dn23:63.3"
msgid ""
