msgstr "silver,"

msgctxt "dn23:64.14"
msgid "pahūtaṃ suvaṇṇaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "and gold abandoned. Seeing it, one friend said to the other:"

msgctxt "dn23:64.15"
msgid ""
"‘yassa kho, samma, atthāya iccheyyāma sāṇaṃ vā sāṇasuttaṃ vā sāṇiyo vā "
"khomaṃ vā khomasuttaṃ vā khomadussaṃ vā kappāsaṃ vā kappāsikasuttaṃ vā "
"kappāsikadussaṃ vā ayaṃ vā lohaṃ vā tipuṃ vā sīsaṃ vā sajjhaṃ vā, idaṃ "
"pahūtaṃ suvaṇṇaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ."
msgstr "‘This pile of gold is just what we wanted all those other things for!"

#. VAR: sajjhabhāraṃ → sajjhuṃ (bj) | sajjhubhāraṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:64.16"
msgid ""
"Tena hi, samma, tvañca sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍehi, ahañca sajjhabhāraṃ chaḍḍessāmi, "
"ubho suvaṇṇabhāraṃ ādāya gamissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Well then, my friend, let’s abandon our bundles, and both take a bundle of "
"gold and go on.’"

msgctxt "dn23:64.17"
msgid ""
"‘Ayaṃ kho me, samma, sāṇabhāro dūrābhato ca susannaddho ca, alaṃ me tvaṃ "
"pajānāhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve already carried this bundle of hemp a long way, and it’s well tied up. "
"It’s good enough for me, you understand.’"

msgctxt "dn23:64.18"
msgid "Atha kho so sahāyako sajjhabhāraṃ chaḍḍetvā suvaṇṇabhāraṃ ādiyi."
msgstr ""
"So one friend abandoned their bundle of silver and picked up a bundle of "
"gold."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.352"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:65.1"
msgid "Te yena sako gāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu."
msgstr "Then they returned to their own village."

msgctxt "dn23:65.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha yo so sahāyako sāṇabhāraṃ ādāya agamāsi, tassa neva mātāpitaro "
"abhinandiṃsu, na puttadārā abhinandiṃsu, na mittāmaccā abhinandiṃsu, na ca "
"tatonidānaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ adhigacchi."
msgstr ""
"When one friend returned with a bundle of sunn hemp, they didn’t please "
"their parents, their partners and children, or their friends and colleagues. "
"And they got no pleasure and happiness on that account."

msgctxt "dn23:65.3"
msgid ""
"Yo pana so sahāyako suvaṇṇabhāraṃ ādāya agamāsi, tassa mātāpitaropi "
"abhinandiṃsu, puttadārāpi abhinandiṃsu, mittāmaccāpi abhinandiṃsu, "
"tatonidānañca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ adhigacchi."
msgstr ""
"But when the other friend returned with a bundle of gold, they pleased their "
"parents, their partners and children, and their friends and colleagues. And "
"they got much pleasure and happiness on that account."

msgctxt "dn23:65.4"
msgid "Evameva kho tvaṃ, rājañña, sāṇabhārikūpamo maññe paṭibhāsi."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, chieftain, you seem like the hemp-carrier in the simile."

msgctxt "dn23:65.5"
msgid "Paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Let go of this harmful misconception, chieftain, let go of it! Don’t create "
"lasting harm and suffering for yourself!”"

msgctxt "dn23:65.6"
msgid "paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:65.7"
msgid "Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:66.1"
msgid "3. Saraṇagamana"
msgstr ""

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="wp" id="wp30"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:67.1"
msgid "“Purimeneva ahaṃ opammena bhoto kassapassa attamano abhiraddho."
msgstr ""
"“I was delighted and satisfied with your very first simile, Master Kassapa!"

msgctxt "dn23:67.2"
msgid ""
"Api cāhaṃ imāni vicitrāni pañhāpaṭibhānāni sotukāmo evāhaṃ bhavantaṃ "
"kassapaṃ paccanīkaṃ kātabbaṃ amaññissaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Nevertheless, I wanted to hear your various solutions to the problem, so I "
"thought I’d oppose you in this way."

msgctxt "dn23:67.3"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho kassapa, abhikkantaṃ, bho kassapa."
msgstr "Excellent, Master Kassapa! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn23:67.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho kassapa, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
msgstr ""
"As if he was righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark  "

msgctxt "dn23:67.5"
msgid "‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;"
msgstr "so people with good eyes can see what’s there,  "

msgctxt "dn23:67.6"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhotā kassapena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "Master Kassapa has made the teaching clear in many ways."

msgctxt "dn23:67.7"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bho kassapa, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, "
"bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the Dharma, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn23:67.8"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ kassapo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Kassapa remember me as a lay follower who "
"has gone for refuge for life."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:68.1"
msgid ""
"Icchāmi cāhaṃ, bho kassapa, mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ, anusāsatu maṃ bhavaṃ "
"kassapo, yaṃ mamassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Master Kassapa, I wish to perform a great sacrifice. Please instruct me so "
"it will be for my lasting welfare and happiness."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:69.1"
msgid "4. Yaññakathā"
msgstr "On Sacrifice"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a><a class="wp" id="wp31"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.353"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:70.1"
msgid ""
"“Yathārūpe kho, rājañña, yaññe gāvo vā haññanti ajeḷakā vā haññanti, "
"kukkuṭasūkarā vā haññanti, vividhā vā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti, paṭiggāhakā "
"ca honti micchādiṭṭhī micchāsaṅkappā micchāvācā micchākammantā micchāājīvā "
"micchāvāyāmā micchāsatī micchāsamādhī, evarūpo kho, rājañña, yañño na "
"mahapphalo hoti na mahānisaṃso na mahājutiko na mahāvipphāro."
msgstr ""
"“Chieftain, take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, "
"chickens and pigs and various kinds of creatures are slaughtered. And the "
"recipients have wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong "
"livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion. That kind "
"of sacrifice is not very fruitful or beneficial or splendid or bountiful."

msgctxt "dn23:70.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājañña, kassako bījanaṅgalaṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya."
msgstr "Suppose a farmer was to enter a wood taking seed and plough."

msgctxt "dn23:70.3"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhette dubbhūme avihatakhāṇukaṇṭake bījāni patiṭṭhāpeyya "
"khaṇḍāni pūtīni vātātapahatāni asāradāni asukhasayitāni."
msgstr ""
"And on that barren field, that barren ground, with uncleared stumps he sowed "
"seeds that were broken, spoiled, weather-damaged, infertile, and ill kept."

msgctxt "dn23:70.4"
msgid "Devo ca na kālena kālaṃ sammādhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya."
msgstr "And the heavens don’t provide enough rain when needed."

#. VAR: virūḷhiṃ → verūḷhiṃ (bj) | viruḷhiṃ (s1-3, km moggalāne)
msgctxt "dn23:70.5"
msgid ""
"Api nu tāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ, kassako vā vipulaṃ "
"phalaṃ adhigaccheyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Would those seeds grow, increase, and mature, and would the farmer get "
"abundant fruit?”"

#. VAR: hidaṃ → na evaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:70.6"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho kassapa”."
msgstr "“No, Master Kassapa.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:71.1"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, rājañña, yathārūpe yaññe gāvo vā haññanti, ajeḷakā vā "
"haññanti, kukkuṭasūkarā vā haññanti, vividhā vā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti, "
"paṭiggāhakā ca honti micchādiṭṭhī micchāsaṅkappā micchāvācā micchākammantā "
"micchāājīvā micchāvāyāmā micchāsatī micchāsamādhī, evarūpo kho, rājañña, "
"yañño na mahapphalo hoti na mahānisaṃso na mahājutiko na mahāvipphāro."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, chieftain, take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats "
"and sheep, chickens and pigs and various kinds of creatures are slaughtered. "
"And the recipients have wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong "
"action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong "
"immersion. That kind of sacrifice is not very fruitful or beneficial or "
"splendid or bountiful."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.354"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:72.1"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpe ca kho, rājañña, yaññe neva gāvo haññanti, na ajeḷakā haññanti, na "
"kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, na vividhā vā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti, paṭiggāhakā "
"ca honti sammādiṭṭhī sammāsaṅkappā sammāvācā sammākammantā sammāājīvā "
"sammāvāyāmā sammāsatī sammāsamādhī, evarūpo kho, rājañña, yañño mahapphalo "
"hoti mahānisaṃso mahājutiko mahāvipphāro."
msgstr ""
"But take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and "
"pigs and various kinds of creatures are not slaughtered. And the recipients "
"have right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right "
"livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. That kind "
"of sacrifice is very fruitful and beneficial and splendid and bountiful."

msgctxt "dn23:72.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājañña, kassako bījanaṅgalaṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya."
msgstr "Suppose a farmer was to enter a wood taking seed and plough."

msgctxt "dn23:72.3"
msgid ""
"So tattha sukhette subhūme suvihatakhāṇukaṇṭake bījāni patiṭṭhapeyya "
"akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sāradāni sukhasayitāni."
msgstr ""
"And on that fertile field, that fertile ground, with well-cleared stumps he "
"sowed seeds that were intact, unspoiled, not weather-damaged, fertile, and "
"well kept."

msgctxt "dn23:72.4"
msgid "Devo ca kālena kālaṃ sammādhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya."
msgstr "And the heavens provide plenty of rain when needed."

msgctxt "dn23:72.5"
msgid ""
"Api nu tāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ, kassako vā vipulaṃ "
"phalaṃ adhigaccheyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Would those seeds grow, increase, and mature, and would the farmer get "
"abundant fruit?”"

msgctxt "dn23:72.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho kassapa”."
msgstr "“Yes, Master Kassapa."

msgctxt "dn23:72.7"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, rājañña, yathārūpe yaññe neva gāvo haññanti, na ajeḷakā "
"haññanti, na kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, na vividhā vā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti, "
"paṭiggāhakā ca honti sammādiṭṭhī sammāsaṅkappā sammāvācā sammākammantā "
"sammāājīvā sammāvāyāmā sammāsatī sammāsamādhī, evarūpo kho, rājañña, yañño "
"mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso mahājutiko mahāvipphāro”ti."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, chieftain, take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats "
"and sheep, chickens and pigs and various kinds of creatures are not "
"slaughtered. And the recipients have right view, right thought, right "
"speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and "
"right immersion. That kind of sacrifice is very fruitful and beneficial and "
"splendid and bountiful.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:73.1"
msgid "5. Uttaramāṇavavatthu"
msgstr "On the Brahmin Student Uttara"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a><a class="wp" id="wp32"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.355"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:74.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pāyāsi rājañño dānaṃ paṭṭhapesi "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇakapaṇaddhikavaṇibbakayācakānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then the chieftain Pāyāsi set up an offering for ascetics and brahmins, for "
"paupers, vagrants, travelers, and beggars."

# Read dhorakani, from dhura (comm thūlāni). For guḷavālakāni, cp. Kd 15 which has macchavāḷaka for a monk's (forbidden) robe. It doesn't make it particularly clear, but at least it's something.
#. VAR: dhorakāni → corakāni (s1-3, km) | therakāni (pts1)
#. VAR: guḷavālakāni → guḷagāḷakāni (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:74.2"
msgid ""
"Tasmiṃ kho pana dāne evarūpaṃ bhojanaṃ dīyati kaṇājakaṃ bilaṅgadutiyaṃ, "
"dhorakāni ca vatthāni guḷavālakāni."
msgstr ""
"At that offering such food as rough gruel with pickles was given, and heavy "
"clothes with ball-tails."

#. VAR: vāvaṭo → byāvaṭo (bj) | vyāvaṭo (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:74.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana dāne uttaro nāma māṇavo vāvaṭo ahosi."
msgstr "Now, it was a brahmin student named Uttara who organized that offering."

msgctxt "dn23:74.4"
msgid "So dānaṃ datvā evaṃ anuddisati:"
msgstr "When the offering was over he referred to it like this:"

msgctxt "dn23:74.5"
msgid ""
"“imināhaṃ dānena pāyāsiṃ rājaññameva imasmiṃ loke samāgacchiṃ, mā "
"parasmin”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Through this offering may I be together with the chieftain Pāyāsi in this "
"world, but not in the next.”"

msgctxt "dn23:74.6"
msgid "Assosi kho pāyāsi rājañño:"
msgstr "Pāyāsi heard of this,"

msgctxt "dn23:74.7"
msgid "“uttaro kira māṇavo dānaṃ datvā evaṃ anuddisati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:74.8"
msgid ""
"‘imināhaṃ dānena pāyāsiṃ rājaññameva imasmiṃ loke samāgacchiṃ, mā "
"parasmin’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:74.9"
msgid "Atha kho pāyāsi rājañño uttaraṃ māṇavaṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca:"
msgstr "so he summoned Uttara and said:"

msgctxt "dn23:74.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, tāta uttara, dānaṃ datvā evaṃ anuddisasi:"
msgstr ""
"“Is it really true, dear Uttara, that you referred to the offering in this "
"way?”"

msgctxt "dn23:74.11"
msgid ""
"‘imināhaṃ dānena pāyāsiṃ rājaññameva imasmiṃ loke samāgacchiṃ, mā "
"parasmin’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:74.12"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn23:74.13"
msgid "“Kissa pana tvaṃ, tāta uttara, dānaṃ datvā evaṃ anuddisasi:"
msgstr "“But why?"

msgctxt "dn23:74.14"
msgid ""
"‘imināhaṃ dānena pāyāsiṃ rājaññameva imasmiṃ loke samāgacchiṃ, mā "
"parasmin’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:74.15"
msgid "Nanu mayaṃ, tāta uttara, puññatthikā dānasseva phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhino”ti?"
msgstr "Don’t we who seek merit expect some result from the offering?”"

#. VAR: pādāpi → pādāsi (mr)
#. VAR: samphusituṃ → phusituṃ (bj) | chupituṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:74.16"
msgid ""
"“Bhoto kho dāne evarūpaṃ bhojanaṃ dīyati kaṇājakaṃ bilaṅgadutiyaṃ, yaṃ "
"bhavaṃ pādāpi na iccheyya samphusituṃ, kuto bhuñjituṃ, dhorakāni ca vatthāni "
"guḷavālakāni, yāni bhavaṃ pādāpi na iccheyya samphusituṃ, kuto paridahituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“At your offering such food as rough gruel with pickles was given, which you "
"wouldn’t even want to touch with your foot, much less eat. And also heavy "
"clothes with ball-tails, which you also wouldn’t want to touch with your "
"foot, much less wear."

msgctxt "dn23:74.17"
msgid ""
"Bhavaṃ kho panamhākaṃ piyo manāpo, kathaṃ mayaṃ manāpaṃ amanāpena "
"saṃyojemā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Sir, you’re dear and beloved to me. But how can I reconcile one so dear with "
"something so disagreeable?”"

msgctxt "dn23:74.18"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi tvaṃ, tāta uttara, yādisāhaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjāmi, tādisaṃ bhojanaṃ "
"paṭṭhapehi."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, dear Uttara, set up an offering with the same kind of food that "
"I eat,"

msgctxt "dn23:74.19"
msgid "Yādisāni cāhaṃ vatthāni paridahāmi, tādisāni ca vatthāni paṭṭhapehī”ti."
msgstr "and the same kind of clothes that I wear.”"

msgctxt "dn23:74.20"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho uttaro māṇavo pāyāsissa rājaññassa paṭissutvā yādisaṃ "
"bhojanaṃ pāyāsi rājañño bhuñjati, tādisaṃ bhojanaṃ paṭṭhapesi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Uttara, and did so."

msgctxt "dn23:74.21"
msgid ""
"Yādisāni ca vatthāni pāyāsi rājañño paridahati, tādisāni ca vatthāni "
"paṭṭhapesi."
msgstr ""

# Cp AN 5.147, AN 9.20
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.356"></a>
#. VAR: acittīkataṃ → apaviddhaṃ (bj) | acittikataṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:75.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pāyāsi rājañño asakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā asahatthā dānaṃ datvā "
"acittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā apaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajji suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"So the chieftain Pāyāsi gave gifts carelessly, thoughtlessly, not with his "
"own hands, giving the dregs. When his body broke up, after death, he was "
"reborn in company with the gods of the Four Great Kings, in an empty palace "
"of acacia."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn23:75.2"
msgid "Yo pana tassa dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:75.3"
msgid ""
"So sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā sahatthā dānaṃ datvā cittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā "
"anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajji devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ."
msgstr ""
"But the brahmin student Uttara who organized the offering gave gifts "
"carefully, thoughtfully, with his own hands, not giving the dregs. When his "
"body broke up, after death, he was reborn in company with the gods of the "
"Thirty-Three."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:76.1"
msgid "6. Pāyāsidevaputta"
msgstr "The God Pāyāsi"

# Contra MW's note, divivihara is usually the day's meditation; siesta is divaseyya
#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a><a class="wp" id="wp33"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.357"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:77.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā gavampati abhikkhaṇaṃ suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ "
"divāvihāraṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Gavampati would often go to that empty acacia "
"palace for the day’s meditation."

msgctxt "dn23:77.2"
msgid "Atha kho pāyāsi devaputto yenāyasmā gavampati tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then the god Pāyāsi went up to him,"

msgctxt "dn23:77.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ gavampatiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "bowed, and stood to one side."

msgctxt "dn23:77.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho pāyāsiṃ devaputtaṃ āyasmā gavampati etadavoca:"
msgstr "Gavampati said to him:"

msgctxt "dn23:77.5"
msgid "“kosi tvaṃ, āvuso”ti?"
msgstr "“Who are you, reverend?”"

msgctxt "dn23:77.6"
msgid "“Ahaṃ, bhante, pāyāsi rājañño”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, I am the chieftain Pāyāsi.”"

msgctxt "dn23:77.7"
msgid "“Nanu tvaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahosi:"
msgstr "“Didn’t you have the view that"

msgctxt "dn23:77.8"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"there’s no afterlife, no beings are reborn spontaneously, and there’s no "
"fruit or result of good and bad deeds?”"

msgctxt "dn23:77.9"
msgid "“Saccāhaṃ, bhante, evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahosiṃ:"
msgstr "“It’s true, sir, I did have such a view."

msgctxt "dn23:77.10"
msgid ""
"‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:77.11"
msgid "Api cāhaṃ ayyena kumārakassapena etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecito”ti."
msgstr ""
"But Venerable Kumāra Kassapa dissuaded me from the harmful misconception.”"

msgctxt "dn23:77.12"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana te, āvuso, dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo, so kuhiṃ "
"upapanno”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But the student named Uttara who organized that offering for you—where has "
"he been reborn?”"

msgctxt "dn23:77.13"
msgid ""
"“Yo me, bhante, dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo, so sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ "
"datvā sahatthā dānaṃ datvā cittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapanno devānaṃ "
"tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, Uttara gave gifts carefully, thoughtfully, with his own hands, not "
"giving the dregs. When his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in "
"company with the gods of the Thirty-Three."

msgctxt "dn23:77.14"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ pana, bhante, asakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā asahatthā dānaṃ datvā acittīkataṃ "
"dānaṃ datvā apaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapanno suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But I gave gifts carelessly, thoughtlessly, not with my own hands, giving "
"the dregs. When my body broke up, after death, I was reborn in company with "
"the gods of the Four Great Kings, in an empty palace of acacia."

msgctxt "dn23:77.15"
msgid "Tena hi, bhante gavampati, manussalokaṃ gantvā evamārocehi:"
msgstr "So, sir, when you’ve returned to the human realm, please announce this:"

msgctxt "dn23:77.16"
msgid ""
"‘sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ detha, sahatthā dānaṃ detha, cittīkataṃ dānaṃ detha, "
"anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ detha."
msgstr ""
"‘Give gifts carefully, thoughtfully, with your own hands, not giving the "
"dregs."

msgctxt "dn23:77.17"
msgid ""
"Pāyāsi rājañño asakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā asahatthā dānaṃ datvā acittīkataṃ "
"dānaṃ datvā apaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapanno suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The chieftain Pāyāsi gave gifts carelessly, thoughtlessly, not with his own "
"hands, giving the dregs. When his body broke up, after death, he was reborn "
"in company with the gods of the Four Great Kings, in an empty palace of "
"acacia."

msgctxt "dn23:77.18"
msgid ""
"Yo pana tassa dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo, so sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā "
"sahatthā dānaṃ datvā cittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa "
"bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapanno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ "
"sahabyatan’”ti."
msgstr ""
"But the brahmin student Uttara who organized the offering gave gifts "
"carefully, thoughtfully, with his own hands, not giving the dregs. When his "
"body broke up, after death, he was reborn in company with the gods of the "
"Thirty-Three.’”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="56"></a><a class="wp" id="wp34"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.358"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:78.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā gavampati manussalokaṃ āgantvā evamārocesi:"
msgstr ""
"So when Venerable Gavampati returned to the human realm he made that "
"announcement."

msgctxt "dn23:78.2"
msgid ""
"“sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ detha, sahatthā dānaṃ detha, cittīkataṃ dānaṃ detha, "
"anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ detha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:78.3"
msgid ""
"Pāyāsi rājañño asakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā asahatthā dānaṃ datvā acittīkataṃ "
"dānaṃ datvā apaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapanno suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn23:78.4"
msgid ""
"Yo pana tassa dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo, so sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā "
"sahatthā dānaṃ datvā cittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa "
"bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapanno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ "
"sahabyatan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn23:79.1"
msgid "Pāyāsisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn23:80.1"
msgid "Mahāvaggo niṭṭhito."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a>
msgctxt "dn23:81.1"
msgid "Mahāpadāna nidānaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn23:81.2"
msgid "nibbānañca sudassanaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn23:81.3"
msgid "Janavasabha govindaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn23:81.4"
msgid "samayaṃ sakkapañhakaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn23:81.5"
msgid "Mahāsatipaṭṭhānañca,"
msgstr ""

